1
00:00:15,140 --> 00:00:18,009
(GBRB: Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

2
00:00:18,010 --> 00:00:20,609
(Lee Kwang Soo)

3
00:00:20,610 --> 00:00:22,709
(Kim Woo Bin)

4
00:00:22,710 --> 00:00:24,949
(Doh Kyung Soo)

5
00:00:24,950 --> 00:00:28,050
(This program contains indirect advertisements.)

6
00:00:29,590 --> 00:00:31,860
(GBRB: Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

7
00:00:32,490 --> 00:00:34,960
(KKPP Food, Day 2 of their technical training)

8
00:00:35,460 --> 00:00:38,159
(A short-term intern joined KKPP to help with the workload.)

9
00:00:38,160 --> 00:00:40,530
We're going to spread it out for the cows.

10
00:00:41,130 --> 00:00:44,300
(The trainees' afternoon assignment)

11
00:00:44,670 --> 00:00:46,970
(Spread garlic husks across a 4,000m² milking barn)

12
00:00:47,570 --> 00:00:50,309
(With more people, the scale of the work also grew.)

13
00:00:50,310 --> 00:00:51,940
As you do it, the work gets exhausting.

14
00:00:52,140 --> 00:00:54,609
(For the exhausted trainees)

15
00:00:54,610 --> 00:00:56,380
CEO Lee, let's make a plan before we continue.

16
00:00:56,480 --> 00:00:57,949
If you win...

17
00:00:57,950 --> 00:01:00,249
(A match began with overtime exemption...)

18
00:01:00,250 --> 00:01:01,750
(and tomorrow's lunch on the line.)

19
00:01:02,350 --> 00:01:05,390
(A yutnori game between KKPP and the ranch)

20
00:01:05,760 --> 00:01:08,490
(The trainees take an early lead.)

21
00:01:09,660 --> 00:01:11,799
(But Team Farm keeps making a comeback.)

22
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:13,860
It's over. It's yut.

23
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:16,899
(KKPP will work overtime spreading garlic husks...)

24
00:01:16,900 --> 00:01:17,970
(and cook tomorrow's lunch.)

25
00:01:18,270 --> 00:01:19,369
Didn't it end so quickly?

26
00:01:19,370 --> 00:01:21,010
It hasn't been long, has it?

27
00:01:21,140 --> 00:01:23,770
Sir, what do you think?

28
00:01:23,870 --> 00:01:25,040
What will you bet on?

29
00:01:29,210 --> 00:01:31,579
If we play one more time, we'll definitely win.

30
00:01:31,580 --> 00:01:32,949
- Right.
- If we play one more round.

31
00:01:32,950 --> 00:01:34,020
What will you bet on?

32
00:01:35,620 --> 00:01:37,620
How about this? If we lose,

33
00:01:38,190 --> 00:01:39,989
we'll do tomorrow's morning task by ourselves.

34
00:01:39,990 --> 00:01:41,090
That sounds good.

35
00:01:41,530 --> 00:01:43,560
- They can sleep in.
- That sounds good.

36
00:01:44,430 --> 00:01:45,460
What if we win?

37
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:49,030
If we win, we'll get what we said earlier.

38
00:01:49,330 --> 00:01:50,799
Sir, we finished discussing.

39
00:01:50,800 --> 00:01:52,370
Can we make a proposal?

40
00:01:53,100 --> 00:01:54,709
We still have work to do,

41
00:01:54,710 --> 00:01:56,369
so we're making a proposal.

42
00:01:56,370 --> 00:01:58,340
Let's reduce the number of pieces to two.

43
00:01:58,840 --> 00:01:59,840
And...

44
00:02:00,580 --> 00:02:02,510
if we lose,

45
00:02:02,980 --> 00:02:06,479
the four of us will do the morning task by ourselves.

46
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:08,720
And you guys can take a break.

47
00:02:09,690 --> 00:02:10,860
All right, let's do that.

48
00:02:12,020 --> 00:02:14,559
(Each team plays 2 pieces. Yellow for KKPP, blue for Team Farm)

49
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:16,890
(Round 2 of yutnori begins.)

50
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:18,160
- Lal.
- Lal.

51
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:21,500
(The first player of Team Farm is Lal.)

52
00:02:24,570 --> 00:02:27,040
- Geol.
- It's geol.

53
00:02:27,340 --> 00:02:29,640
(Geol)

54
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:32,510
(Kyung Soo is up next.)

55
00:02:33,580 --> 00:02:34,580
Nice.

56
00:02:35,010 --> 00:02:36,480
- It's geol. We caught them.
- Catch it.

57
00:02:36,650 --> 00:02:38,019
- It's geol. We caught them.
- Catch it.

58
00:02:38,020 --> 00:02:39,579
(KKPP sends out its first piece.)

59
00:02:39,580 --> 00:02:40,620
We caught them.

60
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:43,049
(He tries to stay calm.)

61
00:02:43,050 --> 00:02:45,090
Let's advance fast, Kyung Soo.

62
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:47,589
(He catches the piece and plays one more time.)

63
00:02:47,590 --> 00:02:49,530
Either gae or geol would work.

64
00:02:50,860 --> 00:02:52,029
- Okay!
- It's mo.

65
00:02:52,030 --> 00:02:53,130
That's great.

66
00:02:53,300 --> 00:02:54,469
(Exclaiming)

67
00:02:54,470 --> 00:02:56,799
(An ominous start)

68
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:59,140
Gae or geol. They're both good.

69
00:03:01,510 --> 00:03:02,510
Back-do.

70
00:03:03,940 --> 00:03:05,779
Should we just move this one?

71
00:03:05,780 --> 00:03:06,879
Yes, that would be better.

72
00:03:06,880 --> 00:03:08,779
Do, gae, geol, yut, mo, back-do.

73
00:03:08,780 --> 00:03:09,780
Yes, let's do that.

74
00:03:10,550 --> 00:03:12,050
That was a clever move.

75
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,880
(The gap is already widening.)

76
00:03:14,550 --> 00:03:17,560
(Kkalloo needs to close the gap immediately.)

77
00:03:20,660 --> 00:03:21,830
- It's a fail.
- A fail.

78
00:03:23,130 --> 00:03:24,130
It's out.

79
00:03:24,131 --> 00:03:26,200
(Making his first mistake at a crucial moment)

80
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:28,199
- Sang Hoon, geol is the best.
- Geol.

81
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,699
- Take it easy.
- Okay.

82
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:30,769
(Do, gae, geol)

83
00:03:30,770 --> 00:03:32,940
(With geol, they can take a shortcut.)

84
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:37,169
(A chance to swing the game in their favor)

85
00:03:37,170 --> 00:03:38,710
(What will be the result?)

86
00:03:41,010 --> 00:03:42,080
- Back-do.
- Back-do.

87
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:46,179
- Okay, it's back-do.
- Back-do.

88
00:03:46,180 --> 00:03:47,380
(Oh, no.)

89
00:03:48,050 --> 00:03:49,050
There's nothing at do.

90
00:03:50,720 --> 00:03:52,789
(He thought that there was a piece at do.)

91
00:03:52,790 --> 00:03:54,860
(Back-do)

92
00:03:54,990 --> 00:03:56,660
You can't be that casual about this.

93
00:03:57,700 --> 00:03:59,860
(Things don't go as planned.)

94
00:04:00,330 --> 00:04:01,670
(It's Team Farm's turn.)

95
00:04:02,830 --> 00:04:04,470
- Gosh.
- It's a fail.

96
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:06,639
- Gosh.
- It's a fail.

97
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:07,669
(Fail)

98
00:04:07,670 --> 00:04:09,270
(It's a fail when it falls within the line.)

99
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:11,480
(Laughing)

100
00:04:11,980 --> 00:04:14,809
(Team Farm hasn't made any move yet.)

101
00:04:14,810 --> 00:04:16,479
- Woo Bin, it's time to pull ahead.
- Okay.

102
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:18,380
(They try to use their chance to run away.)

103
00:04:18,650 --> 00:04:20,679
- It's gae.
- We should advance.

104
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:21,690
Let's keep moving.

105
00:04:22,820 --> 00:04:23,949
- Geol.
- Geol.

106
00:04:23,950 --> 00:04:24,959
This is rough.

107
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:25,990
I'll move it for you.

108
00:04:28,660 --> 00:04:30,259
- Do.
- It's do.

109
00:04:30,260 --> 00:04:31,930
- Shall we start a new piece?
- Let's do that.

110
00:04:32,460 --> 00:04:33,599
We need to catch up to them.

111
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,870
We could also get back-do.

112
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:38,500
(It's Lal's turn again.)

113
00:04:39,370 --> 00:04:40,469
- Do.
- Catch them.

114
00:04:40,470 --> 00:04:42,069
(Do)

115
00:04:42,070 --> 00:04:43,710
- Catch them.
- Do it one more time.

116
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:45,810
I hope that they won't double the piece.

117
00:04:46,580 --> 00:04:47,809
(The piece got caught.)

118
00:04:47,810 --> 00:04:48,949
Lal, play one more time.

119
00:04:48,950 --> 00:04:50,980
(If they get gae, they could double the piece.)

120
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:54,490
(It all comes down to Lal's next move.)

121
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:00,920
- Gae.
- Gae.

122
00:05:00,921 --> 00:05:01,990
Shall we stack our pieces?

123
00:05:04,090 --> 00:05:06,200
Stack the pieces or advance?

124
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:07,900
We should stack the pieces.

125
00:05:07,901 --> 00:05:09,099
- Stack them?
- Yes.

126
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:12,499
(Team Farm makes a daring move by stacking two pieces together.)

127
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:15,110
We have to catch them no matter what. I'm serious.

128
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:17,469
- We have to get geol.
- Geol?

129
00:05:17,470 --> 00:05:18,709
Woo Bin, you might feel pressured,

130
00:05:18,710 --> 00:05:19,880
but you must get geol.

131
00:05:21,580 --> 00:05:23,280
If you don't get geol, we'd lose.

132
00:05:23,310 --> 00:05:24,349
All right.

133
00:05:24,350 --> 00:05:26,050
(KKPP's fate is in Woo Bin's hands.)

134
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:27,719
(The starting point)

135
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:31,090
(Geol is the only way to stop their lead.)

136
00:05:33,660 --> 00:05:35,760
Let it be geol.

137
00:05:39,300 --> 00:05:40,300
- Back-do.
- Back-do.

138
00:05:42,930 --> 00:05:44,470
Let's move this one back.

139
00:05:44,570 --> 00:05:46,500
(A huge grin)

140
00:05:48,070 --> 00:05:50,110
(Moving back 1 space)

141
00:05:51,110 --> 00:05:52,310
Gae would be the best.

142
00:05:55,750 --> 00:05:56,750
It's gae.

143
00:05:56,751 --> 00:05:58,019
(Gae)

144
00:05:58,020 --> 00:05:59,049
- Gae?
- Goodness.

145
00:05:59,050 --> 00:06:01,220
(Once the tide turns...)

146
00:06:02,820 --> 00:06:03,820
Geol?

147
00:06:03,820 --> 00:06:04,820
(Geol)

148
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:07,729
How is this possible?

149
00:06:07,730 --> 00:06:09,759
(Almost at the finish in just 2 moves)

150
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:11,660
(The game flips in an instant.)

151
00:06:12,230 --> 00:06:14,230
We're in trouble. It has to be either gae or geol.

152
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:15,800
What do we do?

153
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:16,800
(Do, gae)

154
00:06:16,801 --> 00:06:18,469
(Do, gae, geol)

155
00:06:18,470 --> 00:06:21,270
(With gae or geol, will they spark a comeback?)

156
00:06:24,740 --> 00:06:25,809
- Geol.
- It's geol.

157
00:06:25,810 --> 00:06:27,709
(Geol)

158
00:06:27,710 --> 00:06:29,980
- Turn this way.
- That's good.

159
00:06:30,780 --> 00:06:33,220
(They have a chance to chase after the opponent.)

160
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:34,919
If they throw less than geol...

161
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:36,089
and we go after them,

162
00:06:36,090 --> 00:06:37,290
- we could catch both of them.
- Right.

163
00:06:37,520 --> 00:06:38,520
Please.

164
00:06:39,260 --> 00:06:41,159
(If they get geol or more, Team Farm will win.)

165
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:43,190
- Try to catch us.
- He stepped on the line.

166
00:06:43,330 --> 00:06:44,330
(He stepped on the line.)

167
00:06:44,331 --> 00:06:46,630
- He stepped on the line.
- I'm sorry, but you're on the line.

168
00:06:46,730 --> 00:06:48,529
(He stepped on the line.)

169
00:06:48,530 --> 00:06:51,100
(Stepping on the line makes it invalid.)

170
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:52,600
All right.

171
00:06:53,700 --> 00:06:56,070
(They barely created a chance.)

172
00:06:56,370 --> 00:06:58,510
- Mr. Lal keeps giving you a look.
- Right.

173
00:06:59,610 --> 00:07:01,550
- I'm sorry, Senior Lal.
- Senior Lal.

174
00:07:02,710 --> 00:07:05,380
Kyung Soo, you know what would happen if we don't get geol?

175
00:07:05,520 --> 00:07:07,850
- My heart is racing.
- This is our last chance.

176
00:07:08,820 --> 00:07:11,259
Please, let it be geol.

177
00:07:11,260 --> 00:07:12,260
(These two pieces will decide the direction of this game.)

178
00:07:12,261 --> 00:07:13,459
Tomorrow, we have to cook...

179
00:07:13,460 --> 00:07:15,590
and come to work at 6am.

180
00:07:16,630 --> 00:07:17,830
Kyung Soo can do this.

181
00:07:18,930 --> 00:07:19,960
It has to be geol.

182
00:07:22,630 --> 00:07:27,099
(This is their last chance to catch two pieces.)

183
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:31,780
(Will they be able to turn the game around?)

184
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:37,680
(Geol)

185
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:40,050
- It's geol.
- Yes!

186
00:07:41,950 --> 00:07:44,089
(Geol appears like a miracle.)

187
00:07:44,090 --> 00:07:45,960
We caught them.

188
00:07:46,820 --> 00:07:48,790
(Geol Kyung Soo pulled it off.)

189
00:07:49,490 --> 00:07:52,760
(Meanwhile, Team Farm is caught right before the finish line.)

190
00:07:53,960 --> 00:07:55,299
We just need to avoid failing.

191
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:57,529
(They take control in an instant.)

192
00:07:57,530 --> 00:07:58,599
Play one more time.

193
00:07:58,600 --> 00:07:59,669
- Just avoid failing.
- Kyung Soo.

194
00:07:59,670 --> 00:08:00,900
- Don't fail.
- Failing would be ridiculous.

195
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:03,670
Wait, don't step on the line.

196
00:08:04,210 --> 00:08:05,380
(A small mistake can be fatal.)

197
00:08:08,950 --> 00:08:12,579
- Gae is good. Take the shortcut.
- Take the shortcut.

198
00:08:12,580 --> 00:08:14,050
- Gae.
- We take the shortcut.

199
00:08:14,150 --> 00:08:16,750
(Their last piece takes the shortcut.)

200
00:08:16,890 --> 00:08:18,089
We won this round.

201
00:08:18,090 --> 00:08:19,090
It's unbelievable.

202
00:08:20,690 --> 00:08:21,859
I'm proud of you.

203
00:08:21,860 --> 00:08:23,430
(KKPP seizes the upper hand.)

204
00:08:25,260 --> 00:08:26,260
A fail.

205
00:08:28,830 --> 00:08:30,400
- Do. No, it's gae.
- Gae.

206
00:08:30,630 --> 00:08:31,670
Stack them.

207
00:08:32,670 --> 00:08:34,669
(Team Farm chases after them until the end.)

208
00:08:34,670 --> 00:08:36,040
We need gae next.

209
00:08:36,470 --> 00:08:37,770
Oh, it's my turn.

210
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:40,240
That startled me.

211
00:08:40,241 --> 00:08:41,479
- Gae.
- Nice.

212
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:44,880
- It's gae.
- Nice.

213
00:08:45,850 --> 00:08:47,779
- Seriously...
- I thought that I failed.

214
00:08:47,780 --> 00:08:48,790
In one go...

215
00:08:55,030 --> 00:08:56,030
Geol.

216
00:08:56,031 --> 00:08:58,329
- Yut.
- We finished.

217
00:08:58,330 --> 00:09:02,700
It's yut. Nice.

218
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:06,369
(KKPP 2: Team Farm 0)

219
00:09:06,370 --> 00:09:08,569
(They won Round 2 thanks to Kyung Soo's performance.)

220
00:09:08,570 --> 00:09:09,670
We got saved.

221
00:09:09,940 --> 00:09:11,009
Goodness.

222
00:09:11,010 --> 00:09:12,039
(A disappointing loss for Team Farm)

223
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:13,680
- Well done.
- You too.

224
00:09:13,780 --> 00:09:15,610
- Good job.
- Thank you.

225
00:09:15,850 --> 00:09:16,850
As promised,

226
00:09:17,550 --> 00:09:20,050
we'll take care of spreading out the garlic husks.

227
00:09:20,150 --> 00:09:23,019
After giving them milk,

228
00:09:23,020 --> 00:09:24,319
you can go home.

229
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:25,619
- Okay.
- All right.

230
00:09:25,620 --> 00:09:28,430
(You finally won. How did you feel?)

231
00:09:28,530 --> 00:09:29,660
I felt so happy.

232
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:32,200
He's really competitive.

233
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:36,829
I guess he usually holds a lot in.

234
00:09:36,830 --> 00:09:39,540
(Laughing)

235
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:41,910
I don't feel...

236
00:09:42,710 --> 00:09:43,710
so good about it.

237
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:47,640
(He won't fall asleep easily tonight.)

238
00:09:48,310 --> 00:09:49,310
Goodness.

239
00:09:50,680 --> 00:09:53,749
(GBRB Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

240
00:09:53,750 --> 00:09:56,449
(Lee Kwang Soo)

241
00:09:56,450 --> 00:09:58,659
(Kim Woo Bin)

242
00:09:58,660 --> 00:10:00,720
(Doh Kyung Soo)

243
00:10:05,260 --> 00:10:07,730
(GBRB Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

244
00:10:07,930 --> 00:10:09,129
Shall we herd them now?

245
00:10:09,130 --> 00:10:10,829
- Yes, let's do that.
- Okay.

246
00:10:10,830 --> 00:10:12,740
(It's time for the grazing cows to head back home.)

247
00:10:13,500 --> 00:10:15,769
(It's the intern's first time herding cows.)

248
00:10:15,770 --> 00:10:17,539
Do we guide them gently...

249
00:10:17,540 --> 00:10:18,679
back over there?

250
00:10:18,680 --> 00:10:20,040
- Gently?
- It won't be gentle.

251
00:10:20,940 --> 00:10:23,310
Once you see them, you'll know what to do.

252
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:26,649
Let's go.

253
00:10:26,650 --> 00:10:27,919
(They enter the pasture to find the dairy cows.)

254
00:10:27,920 --> 00:10:29,450
Let's go home.

255
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:33,560
Kwang Soo, we should go behind and herd them.

256
00:10:34,560 --> 00:10:35,589
Why are there only a few?

257
00:10:35,590 --> 00:10:36,930
Where is everyone?

258
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:39,599
Why are they the only ones here?

259
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:41,470
(Did the dairy cows disappear?)

260
00:10:41,670 --> 00:10:43,729
We should go over there and herd them.

261
00:10:43,730 --> 00:10:45,000
They must be far back there.

262
00:10:45,540 --> 00:10:47,140
- Do they go that far?
- Yes.

263
00:10:47,770 --> 00:10:50,610
(They must be hiding somewhere in the pasture.)

264
00:10:50,870 --> 00:10:52,110
Leave these ones.

265
00:10:52,340 --> 00:10:53,639
You should go over there...

266
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:55,080
- and herd the rest of them.
- Okay.

267
00:10:55,180 --> 00:10:56,180
Do we go around the fence?

268
00:10:56,181 --> 00:10:57,749
Yes, we'll walk.

269
00:10:57,750 --> 00:10:59,620
(They go inside to find the remaining cows.)

270
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:01,790
There's a walking path here.

271
00:11:02,820 --> 00:11:05,320
(They'll take the walking path next to the pasture.)

272
00:11:07,790 --> 00:11:09,329
It feels nice to see everything green.

273
00:11:09,330 --> 00:11:10,730
Yes, I agree.

274
00:11:11,060 --> 00:11:12,630
It's really relaxing.

275
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:14,659
I feel like we're in a movie.

276
00:11:14,660 --> 00:11:16,229
Right. It doesn't feel realistic.

277
00:11:16,230 --> 00:11:17,230
Right.

278
00:11:17,570 --> 00:11:19,140
Sang Hoon, isn't it beautiful here?

279
00:11:19,470 --> 00:11:20,670
Yes, it's very beautiful.

280
00:11:21,370 --> 00:11:22,939
Little flowers are all in bloom.

281
00:11:22,940 --> 00:11:25,009
You're right. Wild flowers.

282
00:11:25,010 --> 00:11:27,940
(They take a moment to look around.)

283
00:11:28,010 --> 00:11:29,679
There are many flowers along the path.

284
00:11:29,680 --> 00:11:32,019
This is a camellia tree.

285
00:11:32,020 --> 00:11:33,249
Is this a camellia tree?

286
00:11:33,250 --> 00:11:34,679
You must like camellia trees.

287
00:11:34,680 --> 00:11:37,219
Yes, it's a camellia tree. Over here...

288
00:11:37,220 --> 00:11:38,959
This will grow up into...

289
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:41,190
CEO Lee, this is hydrangea.

290
00:11:41,630 --> 00:11:42,630
- Hydrangea?
- Yes.

291
00:11:42,730 --> 00:11:43,829
Did you separately...

292
00:11:43,830 --> 00:11:44,860
This is canna.

293
00:11:46,260 --> 00:11:48,799
It's canna, and it's red when it blooms.

294
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:49,800
(He starts explaining every plant.)

295
00:11:49,830 --> 00:11:51,000
Metasequoia trees.

296
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:54,470
You know, the tall roadside trees...

297
00:11:54,570 --> 00:11:55,839
- you see on the mainland.
- Right.

298
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:57,139
This is it.

299
00:11:57,140 --> 00:11:58,810
CEO Lee, take a look at these wild chives.

300
00:11:58,910 --> 00:12:00,779
- Wild chives?
- Yes.

301
00:12:00,780 --> 00:12:03,210
Aren't these what old ladies pick?

302
00:12:03,350 --> 00:12:04,379
There's even a pond.

303
00:12:04,380 --> 00:12:05,480
It's a wetland.

304
00:12:05,880 --> 00:12:07,380
Gosh, there's a pond here.

305
00:12:08,420 --> 00:12:09,519
These are lotus flowers.

306
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:11,050
(A pond where lotus flowers bloom)

307
00:12:11,250 --> 00:12:13,319
CEO Lee, these are Japanese cypress trees.

308
00:12:13,320 --> 00:12:15,089
- Japanese cypress trees?
- I see.

309
00:12:15,090 --> 00:12:16,459
These are all Japanese cypress trees.

310
00:12:16,460 --> 00:12:17,460
(His explanation isn't over yet.)

311
00:12:17,461 --> 00:12:18,960
Cypress trees that release phytoncides.

312
00:12:19,230 --> 00:12:21,300
(Sniffing)

313
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:23,600
I come here to walk with my wife.

314
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:25,370
- I see.
- We walk around here once.

315
00:12:25,740 --> 00:12:27,300
Gosh, what's this?

316
00:12:27,370 --> 00:12:29,110
- What?
- What kind of path is this?

317
00:12:29,210 --> 00:12:31,170
It's a forest trail. We'll go around.

318
00:12:31,370 --> 00:12:33,710
Just walking this path would be relaxing.

319
00:12:33,810 --> 00:12:34,810
Seriously.

320
00:12:35,310 --> 00:12:37,810
Even if we get back late, it's okay. We came here to herd the cows.

321
00:12:38,010 --> 00:12:40,179
- Of course.
- It doesn't matter, right?

322
00:12:40,180 --> 00:12:41,380
The cows must be waiting.

323
00:12:41,950 --> 00:12:43,119
We're here to herd the cows.

324
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:44,419
(The boss is excited to show off the backyard.)

325
00:12:44,420 --> 00:12:46,519
There are fatsia shoots and bracken.

326
00:12:46,520 --> 00:12:47,520
(They arrived deep in the forest.)

327
00:12:47,521 --> 00:12:48,560
They look delicious.

328
00:12:49,130 --> 00:12:50,760
Here they are.

329
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:52,829
(Shouting)

330
00:12:52,830 --> 00:12:53,859
They've been hiding here.

331
00:12:53,860 --> 00:12:55,370
They're looking up while grazing.

332
00:12:56,100 --> 00:12:57,230
You're right.

333
00:12:57,670 --> 00:12:58,839
All of them are here.

334
00:12:58,840 --> 00:12:59,840
(The cows are hiding in a corner of the pasture.)

335
00:12:59,841 --> 00:13:00,969
It must be nice for them...

336
00:13:00,970 --> 00:13:03,369
- because it's spacious.
- Right.

337
00:13:03,370 --> 00:13:04,539
They wouldn't feel confined.

338
00:13:04,540 --> 00:13:05,679
You're right.

339
00:13:05,680 --> 00:13:08,180
(They're enjoying some relaxing time.)

340
00:13:08,380 --> 00:13:10,779
They went into the pasture as deep as possible.

341
00:13:10,780 --> 00:13:11,780
I know.

342
00:13:12,150 --> 00:13:15,150
(They located the cows in the pasture successfully.)

343
00:13:16,190 --> 00:13:17,419
Let's go.

344
00:13:17,420 --> 00:13:20,360
(Now it's really time to head back.)

345
00:13:21,530 --> 00:13:22,859
Let's go.

346
00:13:22,860 --> 00:13:24,459
(They slowly make their way back to the ranch.)

347
00:13:24,460 --> 00:13:25,760
Let's go.

348
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:28,530
- This view is really beautiful.
- Yes.

349
00:13:29,930 --> 00:13:32,699
(Their backs glowing in the sunlight)

350
00:13:32,700 --> 00:13:34,669
They look so pretty from here.

351
00:13:34,670 --> 00:13:37,269
- Right?
- They're shimmering.

352
00:13:37,270 --> 00:13:39,680
With the sunlight reflecting on the cows.

353
00:13:40,180 --> 00:13:42,910
Sang Hoon, can you take a photo of me from behind?

354
00:13:44,980 --> 00:13:47,050
(Click)

355
00:13:48,290 --> 00:13:50,050
This makes a great photo.

356
00:13:51,090 --> 00:13:52,289
I'm happy to see you like it.

357
00:13:52,290 --> 00:13:53,620
(A moment worth keeping in memory)

358
00:13:53,760 --> 00:13:55,529
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

359
00:13:55,530 --> 00:13:57,660
(The walk to home starts with laughter.)

360
00:13:58,860 --> 00:14:00,330
Hey, let's go.

361
00:14:01,870 --> 00:14:03,400
Come on.

362
00:14:03,700 --> 00:14:05,000
Whoa.

363
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:07,370
Come on!

364
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:09,369
(Herding the cows home in their own ways)

365
00:14:09,370 --> 00:14:10,440
Let's go.

366
00:14:10,740 --> 00:14:11,810
Let's go.

367
00:14:12,310 --> 00:14:14,140
- Let's go home.
- Why isn't it moving?

368
00:14:14,240 --> 00:14:16,949
- Let's go. Hey.
- Hey.

369
00:14:16,950 --> 00:14:18,350
(The trainees are now quite skilled at it.)

370
00:14:18,920 --> 00:14:21,450
Let's go. Run!

371
00:14:21,590 --> 00:14:24,120
(Some run ahead with long strides.)

372
00:14:24,420 --> 00:14:25,820
Let's go.

373
00:14:26,720 --> 00:14:29,559
(Some rely on their voice.)

374
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:31,459
Come on.

375
00:14:31,460 --> 00:14:33,660
(Including clumsy rolling of the tongue)

376
00:14:33,730 --> 00:14:35,269
Let's go.

377
00:14:35,270 --> 00:14:37,670
(Thanks to that, the cows keep running along.)

378
00:14:37,830 --> 00:14:39,039
They're getting a good workout.

379
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:40,040
(Laughing)

380
00:14:40,041 --> 00:14:41,300
It makes me feel good.

381
00:14:41,370 --> 00:14:42,840
I'm getting a good leg workout today.

382
00:14:43,370 --> 00:14:46,309
(Everyone including the cows is in a good mood on the way down.)

383
00:14:46,310 --> 00:14:47,780
Kyung Soo, can you block that side?

384
00:14:47,880 --> 00:14:48,880
Okay.

385
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:53,720
(Strangely, there's a group falling behind.)

386
00:14:55,150 --> 00:14:57,220
(They've been keeping distance and following from behind.)

387
00:14:58,120 --> 00:15:00,089
(Panting)

388
00:15:00,090 --> 00:15:01,830
(Especially one person who's struggling)

389
00:15:02,730 --> 00:15:03,959
(Huffing...)

390
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:05,629
(and puffing)

391
00:15:05,630 --> 00:15:06,729
Gosh, this is...

392
00:15:06,730 --> 00:15:08,300
This is really exhausting.

393
00:15:08,870 --> 00:15:10,700
(Sang Hoon is too tired to reply.)

394
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:13,270
(A pasture that's way too big)

395
00:15:13,840 --> 00:15:14,840
(Stumbling)

396
00:15:14,841 --> 00:15:16,340
(And rough ground with holes)

397
00:15:16,540 --> 00:15:18,380
I'm getting a workout here.

398
00:15:18,780 --> 00:15:21,650
(In the middle of an extreme weight training)

399
00:15:21,710 --> 00:15:23,480
Let's go.

400
00:15:24,380 --> 00:15:26,150
Run.

401
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:28,690
We aren't helping them at all.

402
00:15:28,790 --> 00:15:30,720
- What?
- We aren't helping them at all.

403
00:15:31,490 --> 00:15:33,089
Everyone already left.

404
00:15:33,090 --> 00:15:34,120
I know.

405
00:15:35,430 --> 00:15:37,030
I'm very low on electrolytes right now.

406
00:15:38,560 --> 00:15:41,060
I have no idea how the day is passing.

407
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:45,300
Even standing feels difficult.

408
00:15:46,740 --> 00:15:47,970
I realize how impressive it is.

409
00:15:49,970 --> 00:15:52,240
And the farm work...

410
00:15:53,910 --> 00:15:56,080
I'll go and wash my hands.

411
00:15:57,480 --> 00:15:59,549
Gosh, it's really shocking.

412
00:15:59,550 --> 00:16:01,380
(The smell of manure clings to his hands.)

413
00:16:02,350 --> 00:16:03,650
All of them are over there.

414
00:16:03,950 --> 00:16:06,560
(Before they know it, they reach the gate.)

415
00:16:07,090 --> 00:16:08,120
Sang Hoon.

416
00:16:08,790 --> 00:16:10,490
- Yes?
- We have to go now.

417
00:16:10,590 --> 00:16:11,590
Okay.

418
00:16:11,591 --> 00:16:14,400
(Sang Hoon finally makes it.)

419
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:15,630
Let's go.

420
00:16:16,991 --> 00:16:18,269
Hoy!

421
00:16:18,270 --> 00:16:19,469
Sang Hoon, you're good at it.

422
00:16:19,470 --> 00:16:21,200
(Thankfully, the intern has regained strength.)

423
00:16:22,510 --> 00:16:23,669
(They push forward again energetically.)

424
00:16:23,670 --> 00:16:25,839
Let's go.

425
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:28,509
Let's go. Run.

426
00:16:28,510 --> 00:16:30,810
Come on, let's go.

427
00:16:31,673 --> 00:16:34,280
(This time, they move with momentum.)

428
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:36,340
Let's go!

429
00:16:36,850 --> 00:16:38,619
(Running smoothly)

430
00:16:38,620 --> 00:16:39,860
- Let's go.
- Come on.

431
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:41,289
- No.
- Come on.

432
00:16:41,290 --> 00:16:42,459
- No.
- Can you go down?

433
00:16:42,460 --> 00:16:45,560
(Handling the rough path with a hop)

434
00:16:45,960 --> 00:16:48,929
- Hoy!
- Let's go.

435
00:16:48,930 --> 00:16:50,600
(The intern squeezes out the last of his strength.)

436
00:16:51,670 --> 00:16:53,339
(Things seem to be going well until...)

437
00:16:53,340 --> 00:16:54,700
No!

438
00:16:54,970 --> 00:16:56,370
- Let's go.
- Hey.

439
00:16:57,140 --> 00:16:58,839
- No.
- Come on.

440
00:16:58,840 --> 00:16:59,840
(They take a wrong turn.)

441
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:00,840
No.

442
00:17:00,841 --> 00:17:02,980
Come this way.

443
00:17:04,550 --> 00:17:06,250
(Laughing while panting)

444
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:07,850
They aren't here.

445
00:17:08,690 --> 00:17:09,920
We should make way...

446
00:17:10,950 --> 00:17:12,090
and block here.

447
00:17:12,620 --> 00:17:13,660
Go out this way.

448
00:17:14,490 --> 00:17:15,760
Go out this way.

449
00:17:16,260 --> 00:17:18,329
No, go down.

450
00:17:18,330 --> 00:17:20,460
(The trainees handle it quickly.)

451
00:17:20,800 --> 00:17:22,600
- No.
- Let's go.

452
00:17:24,430 --> 00:17:25,770
Let's go.

453
00:17:26,370 --> 00:17:29,610
Let's go. Let's go home.

454
00:17:30,040 --> 00:17:31,940
- Yes.
- Keep going.

455
00:17:32,580 --> 00:17:35,040
Hey!

456
00:17:35,150 --> 00:17:36,949
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

457
00:17:36,950 --> 00:17:38,620
Yes.

458
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:40,619
- Let's go.
- Hey, let's go.

459
00:17:40,620 --> 00:17:42,049
Let's go.

460
00:17:42,050 --> 00:17:44,250
(Every cow including the last one returns home.)

461
00:17:45,050 --> 00:17:46,319
Let's go.

462
00:17:46,320 --> 00:17:47,660
(The intern finishes herding for the first time.)

463
00:17:49,230 --> 00:17:53,230
(Does intern Moon Sang Hoon fit well with KKPP?)

464
00:17:53,660 --> 00:17:54,799
I think he does.

465
00:17:54,800 --> 00:17:55,899
But it's been only a day.

466
00:17:55,900 --> 00:17:58,469
Doesn't it feel like he's been here since yesterday?

467
00:17:58,470 --> 00:18:00,139
With one more person,

468
00:18:00,140 --> 00:18:01,870
the workload definitely feels lighter.

469
00:18:02,370 --> 00:18:03,570
Things are a bit easier.

470
00:18:04,870 --> 00:18:06,810
He's reassuring to have around.

471
00:18:07,340 --> 00:18:08,340
He's a comrade.

472
00:18:09,050 --> 00:18:12,280
(The staff look positively at the hard-working intern.)

473
00:18:12,650 --> 00:18:15,150
Actually, it's harder to ruin your first day.

474
00:18:16,320 --> 00:18:18,860
He didn't make any major mistakes,

475
00:18:19,460 --> 00:18:21,590
but I'll need to keep an eye on him.

476
00:18:22,360 --> 00:18:26,059
What kind of person fits in best at KKPP?

477
00:18:26,060 --> 00:18:27,060
That would be someone...

478
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:32,570
who works quietly and diligently.

479
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:34,040
Honestly,

480
00:18:35,140 --> 00:18:36,540
the best is someone like a cow.

481
00:18:37,870 --> 00:18:40,580
Someone who works quietly without talking back.

482
00:18:41,280 --> 00:18:43,110
He goes in to milk.

483
00:18:43,910 --> 00:18:44,979
He eats snacks.

484
00:18:44,980 --> 00:18:46,079
(We're looking for someone who works like a cow.)

485
00:18:46,080 --> 00:18:47,580
He takes breaks when necessary.

486
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:49,349
Are we doing something else at night?

487
00:18:49,350 --> 00:18:51,390
Yes. Let me explain.

488
00:18:51,820 --> 00:18:53,060
Usually,

489
00:18:53,290 --> 00:18:56,630
we go out and take a look at them at night.

490
00:18:56,990 --> 00:18:59,829
Check if any cows fell like a moment ago.

491
00:18:59,830 --> 00:19:03,369
We must carefully check the cow that fell...

492
00:19:03,370 --> 00:19:05,469
- and see if he's okay.
- Right.

493
00:19:05,470 --> 00:19:08,240
We don't need many people.

494
00:19:08,510 --> 00:19:10,210
Maybe about two people.

495
00:19:10,470 --> 00:19:13,040
Around 9pm,

496
00:19:13,440 --> 00:19:14,579
please check them once.

497
00:19:14,580 --> 00:19:15,609
- Okay.
- We got it.

498
00:19:15,610 --> 00:19:16,910
- All right.
- Okay.

499
00:19:17,710 --> 00:19:19,679
Two people go home right after eating.

500
00:19:19,680 --> 00:19:21,820
The other two do the work before going home.

501
00:19:22,790 --> 00:19:24,449
Let's decide after eating.

502
00:19:24,450 --> 00:19:26,260
We have to decide the game too.

503
00:19:26,560 --> 00:19:28,020
Tonight, the game will take...

504
00:19:28,260 --> 00:19:30,360
- a long time.
- Yes.

505
00:19:30,690 --> 00:19:32,130
- By the way...
- Even if it's tiring...

506
00:19:33,630 --> 00:19:34,900
The work is very demanding.

507
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:36,830
It's a heavy strain...

508
00:19:37,070 --> 00:19:38,799
on my body.

509
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:39,939
(Laughing)

510
00:19:39,940 --> 00:19:41,270
I'm doing my best to hang in there,

511
00:19:41,440 --> 00:19:42,609
but it's very hard.

512
00:19:42,610 --> 00:19:43,610
(A long, exhausting day in many ways)

513
00:19:44,010 --> 00:19:45,340
I didn't expect it to be this tough.

514
00:19:45,510 --> 00:19:48,079
(GBRB Farm Operation - Go Go Farm)

515
00:19:48,080 --> 00:19:49,180
We didn't expect it either.

516
00:19:50,510 --> 00:19:51,980
So this is it.

517
00:19:52,750 --> 00:19:54,019
It's a meat restaurant.

518
00:19:54,020 --> 00:19:55,020
(They arrive at the dinner location.)

519
00:19:55,520 --> 00:19:57,149
Do you like skin-on pork belly or pork shoulder?

520
00:19:57,150 --> 00:19:58,150
I like skin-on pork belly.

521
00:19:58,151 --> 00:19:59,159
- Me too.
- Me too.

522
00:19:59,160 --> 00:20:00,389
- Me too.
- I like skin-on pork belly.

523
00:20:00,390 --> 00:20:01,459
Shall we just get skin-on pork belly?

524
00:20:01,460 --> 00:20:02,460
- That sounds good.
- I'm okay with that.

525
00:20:02,461 --> 00:20:04,360
(A unanimous decision on skin-on pork belly)

526
00:20:04,490 --> 00:20:06,500
How about four orders of skin-on pork belly?

527
00:20:06,860 --> 00:20:08,670
Or should we start with three orders?

528
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:10,200
Sang Hoon.

529
00:20:10,330 --> 00:20:12,199
We're 4, and you want to order 3?

530
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:14,839
I wanted to order three every time.

531
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:15,940
Let's order four in the beginning.

532
00:20:16,070 --> 00:20:18,039
(Everyone thought that they misheard.)

533
00:20:18,040 --> 00:20:20,010
I thought of starting with six orders.

534
00:20:20,480 --> 00:20:23,109
(Sang Hoon is quiet.)

535
00:20:23,215 --> 00:20:24,755
Let's eat and push our limits today.

536
00:20:24,780 --> 00:20:27,950
(Another unanimous decision on 6 servings of black pork)

537
00:20:29,977 --> 00:20:33,260
(The intern secretly licks his lips in regret.)

538
00:20:33,586 --> 00:20:35,656
After hard labor like this,

539
00:20:36,849 --> 00:20:37,929
a drink helps you relax...

540
00:20:37,930 --> 00:20:39,500
and sleep well.

541
00:20:39,860 --> 00:20:41,160
But it's not good for health.

542
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:43,499
How about this?

543
00:20:43,500 --> 00:20:45,469
(How about this?)

544
00:20:45,470 --> 00:20:46,640
Shall we split into teams now?

545
00:20:47,490 --> 00:20:49,589
Are we going separately instead?

546
00:20:49,590 --> 00:20:51,660
Earlier, someone brought up going together.

547
00:20:52,060 --> 00:20:53,060
It was Sang Hoon.

548
00:20:53,660 --> 00:20:55,059
(A proposal for a group night patrol came up.)

549
00:20:55,060 --> 00:20:56,070
Shall we vote on it?

550
00:20:56,870 --> 00:20:58,200
Who wants to go together?

551
00:20:58,600 --> 00:20:59,870
One, two, three.

552
00:21:04,570 --> 00:21:07,180
(This is flustering.)

553
00:21:07,410 --> 00:21:08,539
Why did you suggest it...

554
00:21:08,540 --> 00:21:10,049
- when you didn't want to?
- Let me explain.

555
00:21:10,050 --> 00:21:11,279
After sitting down...

556
00:21:11,280 --> 00:21:12,949
and looking at this spring onion salad,

557
00:21:12,950 --> 00:21:14,280
I changed my mind.

558
00:21:14,450 --> 00:21:17,349
Wasn't it your idea in the first place?

559
00:21:17,350 --> 00:21:19,120
That we should all go together?

560
00:21:20,890 --> 00:21:22,590
I can be a little sly.

561
00:21:23,560 --> 00:21:25,859
Shall we split into those who want to go together...

562
00:21:25,860 --> 00:21:27,700
and those who don't?

563
00:21:28,100 --> 00:21:29,100
Let's do this.

564
00:21:29,430 --> 00:21:31,930
We'll take turns to press the stopwatch.

565
00:21:32,240 --> 00:21:34,399
If you guys win, we'll go together.

566
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:36,170
If we win, only two of us will go.

567
00:21:36,710 --> 00:21:37,870
The two won't be you necessarily.

568
00:21:38,240 --> 00:21:40,139
- Will we play again to decide?
- Yes.

569
00:21:40,140 --> 00:21:41,239
(They will decide how many people go.)

570
00:21:41,240 --> 00:21:42,250
Okay.

571
00:21:42,310 --> 00:21:43,450
We'll press it 1 by 1.

572
00:21:43,550 --> 00:21:44,880
- Ready or not, rock-paper-scissors.
- Ready or not, rock-paper-scissors.

573
00:21:45,880 --> 00:21:46,880
Here I go.

574
00:21:47,380 --> 00:21:49,119
(The 1st attempt by Team Going All 4)

575
00:21:49,120 --> 00:21:50,120
Now.

576
00:21:50,320 --> 00:21:51,320
Five.

577
00:21:51,950 --> 00:21:53,320
That's not bad.

578
00:21:54,460 --> 00:21:57,060
(The 2nd try depends on 0 Boy.)

579
00:21:58,190 --> 00:22:00,060
My gosh.

580
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:01,800
We got it. It's 25.

581
00:22:03,070 --> 00:22:05,300
(The 1st attempt by Team Going Only 2)

582
00:22:07,070 --> 00:22:08,070
Five.

583
00:22:09,740 --> 00:22:10,740
It's neck and neck.

584
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:14,310
(Second attempt in a tight game)

585
00:22:14,680 --> 00:22:15,680
Five.

586
00:22:15,680 --> 00:22:16,680
What?

587
00:22:16,681 --> 00:22:17,809
(All 4 of them got 5.)

588
00:22:17,810 --> 00:22:19,179
This has never happened before.

589
00:22:19,180 --> 00:22:20,180
(All 4 of them got 5.)

590
00:22:20,920 --> 00:22:22,119
Ready or not, rock-paper-scissors.

591
00:22:22,120 --> 00:22:23,989
(Starting Round 2 immediately)

592
00:22:23,990 --> 00:22:26,959
(Team Going All 4)

593
00:22:26,960 --> 00:22:27,960
One.

594
00:22:28,420 --> 00:22:30,330
(Laughing)

595
00:22:30,430 --> 00:22:31,960
(Deeply touched)

596
00:22:32,500 --> 00:22:33,960
No, they'll get zero.

597
00:22:34,060 --> 00:22:35,060
(Team Going All 4: 1)

598
00:22:35,061 --> 00:22:36,069
(Team Going All 4: 1 times 1 is 1.)

599
00:22:36,070 --> 00:22:37,070
One.

600
00:22:37,270 --> 00:22:38,469
You just need to avoid zero.

601
00:22:38,470 --> 00:22:39,570
Just avoid zero.

602
00:22:40,340 --> 00:22:41,670
I just need to avoid getting zero.

603
00:22:42,810 --> 00:22:44,469
- Zero.
- Three.

604
00:22:44,470 --> 00:22:46,210
The game is over. We won.

605
00:22:46,910 --> 00:22:48,439
(Team Going Only 2: 3)

606
00:22:48,440 --> 00:22:51,680
(Team Going Only 2: 3 times 0 is 0.)

607
00:22:52,920 --> 00:22:56,520
(Kwang Soo got 0 when they almost had it.)

608
00:22:57,690 --> 00:23:00,019
(CEO Lee...)

609
00:23:00,020 --> 00:23:01,090
I'm really sorry.

610
00:23:01,560 --> 00:23:02,560
I'm sorry.

611
00:23:03,160 --> 00:23:04,160
I'm really sorry.

612
00:23:04,430 --> 00:23:05,430
I'm sorry.

613
00:23:05,490 --> 00:23:07,260
I was going to order some soju.

614
00:23:08,330 --> 00:23:10,700
I nearly ordered it.

615
00:23:12,600 --> 00:23:13,769
How could you get zero?

616
00:23:13,770 --> 00:23:14,770
(Completely humiliated)

617
00:23:15,370 --> 00:23:17,470
Let's go there together. After that...

618
00:23:17,740 --> 00:23:20,080
- The four of us? That's fine.
- Yes.

619
00:23:20,480 --> 00:23:21,540
It won't be just us.

620
00:23:21,780 --> 00:23:23,679
- That looks insane.
- It looks amazing.

621
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:25,720
Gosh, that's what I told you about.

622
00:23:25,820 --> 00:23:26,820
Meat that's stamped.

623
00:23:27,920 --> 00:23:28,920
It looks delicious.

624
00:23:29,150 --> 00:23:30,150
Thank you.

625
00:23:31,050 --> 00:23:32,789
Do you want to switch seats with me?

626
00:23:32,790 --> 00:23:34,290
- What for?
- I'll grill the meat here.

627
00:23:36,730 --> 00:23:40,600
(When the youngest members who are serious about food sit by the grill)

628
00:23:42,260 --> 00:23:43,269
Oh, my.

629
00:23:43,270 --> 00:23:44,669
(A black pork gourmet lesson begins.)

630
00:23:44,670 --> 00:23:46,199
The meat is really thick.

631
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:47,300
(A black pork gourmet lesson begins.)

632
00:23:47,870 --> 00:23:49,440
You grill white kimchi?

633
00:23:49,670 --> 00:23:51,239
That's quite unusual.

634
00:23:51,240 --> 00:23:52,840
(Lesson one: Put everything possible on the grill.)

635
00:23:53,140 --> 00:23:55,380
(When Kyung Soo put on white kimchi and bracken)

636
00:23:56,780 --> 00:23:58,610
You sprinkle black pepper on it?

637
00:23:59,080 --> 00:24:01,050
I didn't know about that.

638
00:24:02,420 --> 00:24:03,990
I can't resist it from looking at it.

639
00:24:06,020 --> 00:24:09,329
(Their mouths are watering.)

640
00:24:09,330 --> 00:24:10,489
It looks so good.

641
00:24:10,490 --> 00:24:11,590
It looks delicious.

642
00:24:12,060 --> 00:24:14,330
Kwang Soo, how will you eat your first piece?

643
00:24:14,760 --> 00:24:15,770
I'll dip it only in salt.

644
00:24:16,070 --> 00:24:17,269
- Only salt?
- Yes.

645
00:24:17,270 --> 00:24:20,100
I can eat it with each one of them.

646
00:24:20,600 --> 00:24:21,800
I want to eat it in a wrap.

647
00:24:22,410 --> 00:24:23,510
The perfect piece.

648
00:24:24,040 --> 00:24:26,010
What will you put in your wrap?

649
00:24:26,610 --> 00:24:28,009
- I'll dip it in salted anchovies.
- Okay.

650
00:24:28,010 --> 00:24:29,379
I'll add this and that.

651
00:24:29,380 --> 00:24:31,480
- And some rice.
- Okay.

652
00:24:32,010 --> 00:24:33,020
You know what?

653
00:24:33,850 --> 00:24:35,549
My first goal is...

654
00:24:35,550 --> 00:24:37,049
stuffing my mouth.

655
00:24:37,050 --> 00:24:38,350
- Like this.
- With water oozing out?

656
00:24:39,060 --> 00:24:40,890
- Is water oozing out?
- Yes.

657
00:24:41,890 --> 00:24:43,129
(A vivid first-bite imagination drill)

658
00:24:43,130 --> 00:24:44,229
Without rice?

659
00:24:44,230 --> 00:24:45,259
- With rice.
- I see.

660
00:24:45,260 --> 00:24:46,829
The color looks delicious.

661
00:24:46,830 --> 00:24:48,559
(Meanwhile, the black pork is grilled crispy.)

662
00:24:48,560 --> 00:24:49,770
When I grill meat,

663
00:24:50,300 --> 00:24:53,270
I look for a piece that catches my eye.

664
00:24:53,700 --> 00:24:55,439
- That one piece.
- I see what you mean.

665
00:24:55,440 --> 00:24:57,039
I pick the best piece...

666
00:24:57,040 --> 00:24:58,509
in my mind.

667
00:24:58,510 --> 00:25:00,609
Here's what I do.

668
00:25:00,610 --> 00:25:03,080
I steer it near me.

669
00:25:03,480 --> 00:25:05,680
The piece that catches my eye.

670
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:07,750
I put it near me.

671
00:25:08,250 --> 00:25:09,989
What if someone eats it instead?

672
00:25:09,990 --> 00:25:12,519
That's why I try to hide it...

673
00:25:12,520 --> 00:25:14,789
- You hide it?
- as much as possible.

674
00:25:14,790 --> 00:25:15,929
Which one is it?

675
00:25:15,930 --> 00:25:17,929
- I haven't found it yet.
- No?

676
00:25:17,930 --> 00:25:20,559
- Can I pick mine?
- Sure.

677
00:25:20,560 --> 00:25:22,669
- Can I pick this one?
- Yes, that looks great.

678
00:25:22,670 --> 00:25:25,170
I'll take good care of it.

679
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:27,699
It has the right amount of cartilage,

680
00:25:27,700 --> 00:25:29,310
and I like the thick part.

681
00:25:29,740 --> 00:25:30,740
What about you, Woo Bin?

682
00:25:31,540 --> 00:25:32,540
For me...

683
00:25:32,541 --> 00:25:34,509
(Woo Bin's pick)

684
00:25:34,510 --> 00:25:35,849
This one? That's nice.

685
00:25:35,850 --> 00:25:37,010
(Once each senior picks his favorite)

686
00:25:38,280 --> 00:25:40,420
I'll pick this one.

687
00:25:41,180 --> 00:25:42,890
(Sang Hoon's pick)

688
00:25:43,120 --> 00:25:44,490
(Exclaiming)

689
00:25:46,590 --> 00:25:47,719
The meat is ready to eat.

690
00:25:47,720 --> 00:25:49,130
You can eat it now.

691
00:25:49,390 --> 00:25:51,130
- Enjoy your food.
- Thank you.

692
00:25:51,330 --> 00:25:53,160
- Enjoy your food.
- Thank you.

693
00:25:53,500 --> 00:25:54,829
Kwang Soo, this is yours.

694
00:25:54,830 --> 00:25:56,369
(Kwang Soo's pick, Sang Hoon's pick)

695
00:25:56,370 --> 00:25:57,429
I'll take this.

696
00:25:57,430 --> 00:25:59,300
(Did he grab Sang Hoon's meat?)

697
00:25:59,600 --> 00:26:00,600
(Kwang Soo, this is yours.)

698
00:26:00,601 --> 00:26:01,840
(I'll take this.)

699
00:26:05,410 --> 00:26:08,810
(The intern's meat gets stolen right in front of him.)

700
00:26:09,950 --> 00:26:12,180
(The meat is already gone.)

701
00:26:13,680 --> 00:26:16,419
(He's left with scars.)

702
00:26:16,420 --> 00:26:18,250
Oh, my.

703
00:26:19,020 --> 00:26:21,590
My mouth is watering so much.

704
00:26:22,120 --> 00:26:24,360
(Hearing how his meat tastes from someone else's mouth)

705
00:26:25,090 --> 00:26:27,700
(The seniors take their piece fast in case it gets stolen.)

706
00:26:31,830 --> 00:26:32,840
My goodness.

707
00:26:33,100 --> 00:26:37,140
(The last lesson: Handle your meat with care.)

708
00:26:37,610 --> 00:26:40,140
(He takes another piece and starts eating.)

709
00:26:41,610 --> 00:26:42,879
(Humming)

710
00:26:42,880 --> 00:26:45,110
- It's really good.
- It tastes completely different.

711
00:26:45,410 --> 00:26:48,020
My mouth is watering so much.

712
00:26:48,750 --> 00:26:51,220
(Savoring it)

713
00:26:51,350 --> 00:26:53,590
The meat flavor fills...

714
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:57,560
Gosh, it tastes really good.

715
00:26:58,160 --> 00:27:00,030
- It's different from pork belly.
- Is it?

716
00:27:01,830 --> 00:27:03,929
(One bite with lettuce)

717
00:27:03,930 --> 00:27:04,930
My gosh.

718
00:27:04,931 --> 00:27:06,600
(Another bite with green onion kimchi)

719
00:27:07,470 --> 00:27:09,039
(A third bite with grilled white kimchi)

720
00:27:09,040 --> 00:27:10,239
This is so good.

721
00:27:10,240 --> 00:27:11,610
(A third bite with grilled white kimchi)

722
00:27:12,010 --> 00:27:13,080
My blood is circulating again.

723
00:27:13,540 --> 00:27:14,779
I was feeling dizzy earlier.

724
00:27:14,780 --> 00:27:15,950
- Now that I'm eating...
- Right?

725
00:27:16,380 --> 00:27:17,949
I feel completely recharged.

726
00:27:17,950 --> 00:27:20,320
(I feel completely recharged.)

727
00:27:21,080 --> 00:27:22,919
The meat tastes really good.

728
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:25,350
(As he imagined, he stuffs his mouth with a wrap.)

729
00:27:25,890 --> 00:27:26,890
Gosh.

730
00:27:28,690 --> 00:27:29,690
Goodness.

731
00:27:29,691 --> 00:27:31,129
(It tastes so good that you forget to wipe your mouth.)

732
00:27:31,130 --> 00:27:32,330
It's really good.

733
00:27:33,230 --> 00:27:34,660
Seriously, it tastes amazing.

734
00:27:36,800 --> 00:27:37,869
Here you go.

735
00:27:37,870 --> 00:27:40,240
(They couldn't resist drinking soju with the meat.)

736
00:27:40,370 --> 00:27:41,740
Let's toast.

737
00:27:42,040 --> 00:27:43,110
Since our intern is here too.

738
00:27:43,170 --> 00:27:45,209
(A toast is a must during a company meal.)

739
00:27:45,210 --> 00:27:46,740
- Give us a leading speech.
- Okay.

740
00:27:48,080 --> 00:27:49,549
Thanks for your hard work today.

741
00:27:49,550 --> 00:27:51,649
I'll be in your care until tomorrow.

742
00:27:51,650 --> 00:27:53,250
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

743
00:27:54,650 --> 00:27:59,420
(The seniors get into the mood with soft drinks.)

744
00:28:03,360 --> 00:28:05,430
- Do you like it?
- Yes.

745
00:28:05,760 --> 00:28:06,929
Does it wash it down?

746
00:28:06,930 --> 00:28:08,500
(Kyung Soo nods.)

747
00:28:09,160 --> 00:28:11,170
It's so sweet.

748
00:28:11,600 --> 00:28:15,340
(It tastes sweeter after tough labor.)

749
00:28:16,410 --> 00:28:20,140
(Finishing the meal nicely with bibim guksu)

750
00:28:20,510 --> 00:28:22,750
(Sang Hoon hums.)

751
00:28:23,150 --> 00:28:24,450
We ate a lot.

752
00:28:24,980 --> 00:28:27,820
(The grill is almost cleared of food.)

753
00:28:28,050 --> 00:28:31,620
Nothing would've tasted better than this today.

754
00:28:32,090 --> 00:28:34,590
It's a perfect way to end the day.

755
00:28:35,120 --> 00:28:36,189
Thanks for the food.

756
00:28:36,190 --> 00:28:37,459
- Thanks for the food.
- Thanks for the food.

757
00:28:37,460 --> 00:28:38,730
(The black pork company meal ends.)

758
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:45,600
(The dinner was perfect from start to finish.)

759
00:28:46,270 --> 00:28:47,569
Hello.

760
00:28:47,570 --> 00:28:48,600
(They stop by a convenience store before the night patrol.)

761
00:28:49,340 --> 00:28:50,469
I've never seen this before.

762
00:28:50,470 --> 00:28:51,470
(They first head to the snacks section.)

763
00:28:51,471 --> 00:28:53,109
- We should buy this.
- We should.

764
00:28:53,110 --> 00:28:55,609
Honestly, I thought yesterday that we should've bought two.

765
00:28:55,610 --> 00:28:57,050
- We should buy this.
- It wasn't enough yesterday.

766
00:28:57,950 --> 00:28:59,380
This is very tasty too.

767
00:29:00,050 --> 00:29:01,580
- It's very precise.
- Shall we get one?

768
00:29:01,680 --> 00:29:03,450
Shall we eat this first and then have that?

769
00:29:04,050 --> 00:29:05,950
Or one each? Should we mix them?

770
00:29:06,420 --> 00:29:08,260
Shall we eat until we can't open our eyes tomorrow?

771
00:29:08,590 --> 00:29:10,489
- Tomorrow morning...
- I can eat...

772
00:29:10,490 --> 00:29:12,759
- until I can't open my eyes.
- For real.

773
00:29:12,760 --> 00:29:15,100
Kwang Soo, after the salty snack,

774
00:29:15,360 --> 00:29:17,199
if you melt this sweet snack in your mouth, it tastes amazing.

775
00:29:17,200 --> 00:29:18,200
Seriously.

776
00:29:18,200 --> 00:29:19,200
(Honey-flavored snack)

777
00:29:19,201 --> 00:29:21,770
- It acts as a cleanser.
- Right.

778
00:29:22,140 --> 00:29:24,170
- Like a bidet.
- Oh? Yes.

779
00:29:24,970 --> 00:29:26,609
Do you not fancy this kind of sweetness?

780
00:29:26,610 --> 00:29:28,609
- That's nice too.
- This feels kind of cold...

781
00:29:28,610 --> 00:29:30,049
- when you chew it, you know that?
- I know what you mean.

782
00:29:30,050 --> 00:29:31,349
It's a chocolate snack,

783
00:29:31,350 --> 00:29:32,780
but strangely, it feels cold.

784
00:29:33,020 --> 00:29:34,249
- I know what you mean.
- Can we buy one...

785
00:29:34,250 --> 00:29:35,649
and put it in the freezer?

786
00:29:35,650 --> 00:29:37,019
- That sounds amazing.
- Right.

787
00:29:37,020 --> 00:29:38,419
- Let's end it with that.
- Okay, I'll do that.

788
00:29:38,420 --> 00:29:40,589
The air in between each layer.

789
00:29:40,590 --> 00:29:42,259
- Yes. Feeling cold, right?
- How should I say this?

790
00:29:42,260 --> 00:29:43,590
- It feels like an AC.
- That's right.

791
00:29:43,830 --> 00:29:46,300
We didn't check out the shelf behind.

792
00:29:46,830 --> 00:29:48,029
This isn't too bad either.

793
00:29:48,030 --> 00:29:50,170
We could dip it into the milk.

794
00:29:50,970 --> 00:29:52,200
- Let's taste it.
- You're right.

795
00:29:53,470 --> 00:29:54,799
(Woo Bin laughs.)

796
00:29:54,800 --> 00:29:55,840
Shall I bring another basket?

797
00:29:55,970 --> 00:29:57,069
- No.
- Okay.

798
00:29:57,070 --> 00:29:58,070
There's too much.

799
00:29:58,170 --> 00:30:00,280
Will you cook it or eat cup noodles?

800
00:30:00,540 --> 00:30:02,009
(Next is the ramyeon section.)

801
00:30:02,010 --> 00:30:03,010
What do you want to eat?

802
00:30:04,080 --> 00:30:06,080
I want the spicy ramyeon.

803
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:07,480
What about you?

804
00:30:07,650 --> 00:30:08,819
- Or jjajang ramyeon.
- I'll go with that too.

805
00:30:08,820 --> 00:30:10,689
- The spicy ramyeon?
- But today,

806
00:30:10,690 --> 00:30:12,220
I kind of feel like going all out.

807
00:30:13,020 --> 00:30:14,119
For example, this.

808
00:30:14,120 --> 00:30:15,519
