809
00:30:15,520 --> 00:30:16,530
With tuna?

810
00:30:16,690 --> 00:30:18,030
Tuna is protein.

811
00:30:19,060 --> 00:30:20,559
Add this to the ramyeon,

812
00:30:20,560 --> 00:30:22,060
- and it tastes incredible.
- It's amazing.

813
00:30:22,130 --> 00:30:23,369
- I agree.
- Which one?

814
00:30:23,370 --> 00:30:24,999
Tuna kimchi jjigae ramyeon.

815
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:26,000
(He timidly recommends the kimchi jjigae ramyeon.)

816
00:30:26,140 --> 00:30:28,270
But if we take that, we'll be going way overboard.

817
00:30:29,670 --> 00:30:30,770
But it's protein.

818
00:30:31,310 --> 00:30:32,569
Woo Bin likes...

819
00:30:32,570 --> 00:30:33,779
(Kyung Soo laughs.)

820
00:30:33,780 --> 00:30:36,450
(Seaweed ramyeon?)

821
00:30:38,250 --> 00:30:39,850
What's that?

822
00:30:40,320 --> 00:30:41,819
It's actually delicious, you know?

823
00:30:41,820 --> 00:30:43,390
- I don't know.
- It's delicious.

824
00:30:43,990 --> 00:30:46,219
Is this a bit too heavy, Kyung Soo?

825
00:30:46,220 --> 00:30:47,289
- Not at all.
- You're okay with it?

826
00:30:47,290 --> 00:30:48,419
- Sang Hoon.
- Then let's go with this.

827
00:30:48,420 --> 00:30:50,489
Three ramyeon plus one tuna can...

828
00:30:50,490 --> 00:30:51,989
- is a perfect combo.
- This is nice.

829
00:30:51,990 --> 00:30:53,000
Okay.

830
00:30:55,500 --> 00:30:56,930
You're so mischievous.

831
00:30:57,700 --> 00:30:58,700
Let's have this.

832
00:30:59,400 --> 00:31:00,439
How many packs?

833
00:31:00,440 --> 00:31:01,799
- Three.
- Sounds good.

834
00:31:01,800 --> 00:31:03,009
Three, and let's get one of these.

835
00:31:03,010 --> 00:31:04,110
- Okay.
- Tuna?

836
00:31:04,670 --> 00:31:06,039
- This tuna?
- Yes.

837
00:31:06,040 --> 00:31:07,040
Okay.

838
00:31:07,380 --> 00:31:08,380
- By the way, - Yes.

839
00:31:08,381 --> 00:31:10,010
will we be having ice cream on our way back?

840
00:31:10,510 --> 00:31:11,510
(Sang Hoon exclaims.)

841
00:31:11,511 --> 00:31:13,220
I would've been disappointed if you didn't ask.

842
00:31:14,136 --> 00:31:15,519
Because one of the reasons...

843
00:31:15,520 --> 00:31:16,889
I wanted to come here was ice cream.

844
00:31:16,890 --> 00:31:18,820
Do you crave creamy ice cream or sherbet?

845
00:31:19,990 --> 00:31:20,990
(Kwang Soo is conflicted.)

846
00:31:20,991 --> 00:31:23,090
(The hardest choice to make in his life)

847
00:31:25,460 --> 00:31:26,460
What about this?

848
00:31:26,813 --> 00:31:28,253
- Like this.
- It's Twin Pops.

849
00:31:28,360 --> 00:31:30,600
I don't mind the taste, I just want to win...

850
00:31:31,300 --> 00:31:32,300
the match.

851
00:31:32,800 --> 00:31:34,169
(Kyung Soo chose Twin Pops.)

852
00:31:34,170 --> 00:31:35,300
Actually,

853
00:31:35,470 --> 00:31:37,669
- think about this too.
- Right.

854
00:31:37,670 --> 00:31:41,140
Because the taste from the meal is still lingering in our mouths.

855
00:31:41,780 --> 00:31:44,110
Eating that would make you feel like you're brushing teeth.

856
00:31:44,680 --> 00:31:47,149
- It refreshes your mouth.
- Exactly.

857
00:31:47,150 --> 00:31:48,150
(The intern's outstanding taste evaluation)

858
00:31:48,151 --> 00:31:49,220
What will you eat, Sang Hoon?

859
00:31:49,320 --> 00:31:51,620
Since I'm in Jeju Island, and Boo is a Jeju Island surname,

860
00:31:51,950 --> 00:31:53,190
I'll go with Bravo Cone.

861
00:31:54,090 --> 00:31:55,560
We bought so much?

862
00:31:56,060 --> 00:31:57,660
(It's time to pay now.)

863
00:31:57,890 --> 00:32:00,059
Shall we do this? Buy one chocolate and...

864
00:32:00,060 --> 00:32:01,959
- There are two in the fridge.
- play rock-paper-scissors.

865
00:32:01,960 --> 00:32:03,670
The winner puts it straight into his mouth.

866
00:32:04,500 --> 00:32:05,800
That sounds good to me.

867
00:32:06,030 --> 00:32:07,969
- What do you think?
- We have chocolates in the fridge.

868
00:32:07,970 --> 00:32:09,040
I want to have it now.

869
00:32:10,570 --> 00:32:11,570
No.

870
00:32:12,570 --> 00:32:13,580
Let's follow the majority.

871
00:32:14,310 --> 00:32:15,809
Who wants to do it now, raise your hand.

872
00:32:15,810 --> 00:32:17,009
Who wants to eat chocolate now?

873
00:32:17,010 --> 00:32:18,080
- One, two, three.
- One, two, three.

874
00:32:20,850 --> 00:32:23,289
(Laughing)

875
00:32:23,290 --> 00:32:24,920
(He fails to hold his laughter.)

876
00:32:25,650 --> 00:32:27,720
But we three talked about it.

877
00:32:28,390 --> 00:32:31,690
(The convenience store shopping ends with Kwang Soo feeling hurt.)

878
00:32:32,060 --> 00:32:34,759
Kyung Soo, let's play the Twin Pops before we get in.

879
00:32:34,760 --> 00:32:35,799
Okay.

880
00:32:35,800 --> 00:32:37,199
Woo Bin. Just hold it,

881
00:32:37,200 --> 00:32:38,570
and we'll pull on the count of three.

882
00:32:38,870 --> 00:32:39,900
One, two, three.

883
00:32:41,170 --> 00:32:42,499
(Kyung Soo laughs happily.)

884
00:32:42,500 --> 00:32:43,510
(I won.)

885
00:32:45,270 --> 00:32:47,310
Are you happy? Are you?

886
00:32:47,840 --> 00:32:50,210
(It was an intense fight.)

887
00:32:51,210 --> 00:32:52,949
- It's tasty, right?
- It is.

888
00:32:52,950 --> 00:32:54,680
(They head back to the farm for the night patrol.)

889
00:32:56,320 --> 00:32:59,620
(Munching)

890
00:32:59,990 --> 00:33:02,259
Sang Hoon, your chewing sounds very delicious.

891
00:33:02,260 --> 00:33:03,290
Why is it so loud?

892
00:33:04,190 --> 00:33:06,860
(Chewing quietly)

893
00:33:07,200 --> 00:33:09,160
What a long day it has been.

894
00:33:09,360 --> 00:33:10,830
What do we need to do now?

895
00:33:12,100 --> 00:33:14,099
You need to go out at night once in a while...

896
00:33:14,100 --> 00:33:16,099
(The night patrol duty they were assigned in the afternoon)

897
00:33:16,100 --> 00:33:18,339
There's a lot of their food up there.

898
00:33:18,340 --> 00:33:21,509
- Clean the barn with the rod.
- Clean the barn?

899
00:33:21,510 --> 00:33:24,309
Check if any cows fell like a moment ago.

900
00:33:24,310 --> 00:33:27,519
Check the temperature of the milk cooling tank....

901
00:33:27,520 --> 00:33:29,119
- because it should be maintained...
- Check the temperature?

902
00:33:29,120 --> 00:33:30,720
- below 5°C.
- Okay.

903
00:33:33,420 --> 00:33:35,720
(At 8:30pm, they arrive at the farm.)

904
00:33:37,860 --> 00:33:39,560
The red lights are scary.

905
00:33:40,060 --> 00:33:41,600
Sang Hoon, do you believe in ghosts?

906
00:33:41,700 --> 00:33:44,230
I can't handle scary stuff.

907
00:33:45,830 --> 00:33:48,970
(They get out of the car.)

908
00:33:50,310 --> 00:33:51,310
What is it suddenly?

909
00:33:53,810 --> 00:33:56,910
(They get out of the car.)

910
00:33:58,150 --> 00:33:59,310
What is it suddenly?

911
00:34:00,380 --> 00:34:02,480
Why did they decide to go with red?

912
00:34:05,820 --> 00:34:10,360
(The farm turns red at night.)

913
00:34:10,830 --> 00:34:12,290
This isn't a haunted house, is it?

914
00:34:13,700 --> 00:34:15,000
It looks like cows would suddenly start speaking.

915
00:34:16,930 --> 00:34:18,100
- There's no way.
- It's scary.

916
00:34:20,270 --> 00:34:21,840
- It's really...
- We'll follow you until here.

917
00:34:22,200 --> 00:34:23,470
- But...
- The night...

918
00:34:24,910 --> 00:34:26,140
Do we film like this?

919
00:34:26,410 --> 00:34:27,579
Do I film my face?

920
00:34:27,580 --> 00:34:28,580
(They need to self-film now.)

921
00:34:28,780 --> 00:34:30,749
Yes, film your face.

922
00:34:30,750 --> 00:34:32,649
(For the next 5 minutes, many clips will be from the self-filmed shots.)

923
00:34:32,650 --> 00:34:34,649
(We apologize in advance for the dark and rough clips.)

924
00:34:34,650 --> 00:34:35,750
We'll get going.

925
00:34:36,490 --> 00:34:37,490
It's scary.

926
00:34:37,720 --> 00:34:39,789
It's way too dark, isn't it?

927
00:34:39,790 --> 00:34:41,420
Why are the lights red?

928
00:34:43,330 --> 00:34:46,230
They didn't plan this to jump scare us, did they?

929
00:34:46,760 --> 00:34:47,760
Let's go.

930
00:34:48,060 --> 00:34:49,100
What's that?

931
00:34:49,460 --> 00:34:50,799
- You're scaring me.
- What is it?

932
00:34:50,800 --> 00:34:52,099
(Milk cooling tank, dairy barn, juvenile cows, calves)

933
00:34:52,100 --> 00:34:53,199
Don't do that.

934
00:34:53,200 --> 00:34:54,270
It feels like someone will be there.

935
00:34:54,800 --> 00:34:57,470
(They face the hardship as soon as they take the first step.)

936
00:34:58,770 --> 00:35:00,540
(Kwang Soo is scared.)

937
00:35:00,580 --> 00:35:02,780
(He was startled by his own shadow.)

938
00:35:03,480 --> 00:35:04,480
It's so scary.

939
00:35:05,680 --> 00:35:07,119
Will you go to Gogo and Farmfarm?

940
00:35:07,120 --> 00:35:08,120
Shall we visit them first?

941
00:35:08,121 --> 00:35:10,220
Let's check how they're doing.

942
00:35:11,420 --> 00:35:12,420
It's cold.

943
00:35:12,650 --> 00:35:16,529
(They arrived at the calves' barn.)

944
00:35:16,530 --> 00:35:17,630
They're all asleep.

945
00:35:18,660 --> 00:35:20,300
- They're all lying down.
- So cute.

946
00:35:21,400 --> 00:35:22,430
They are.

947
00:35:23,270 --> 00:35:24,400
Are Gogo and Farmfarm doing well?

948
00:35:24,430 --> 00:35:26,029
- Yes, they're all here.
- Okay.

949
00:35:26,030 --> 00:35:27,170
They're sitting down and looking at us.

950
00:35:28,700 --> 00:35:29,910
Good night, guys.

951
00:35:30,410 --> 00:35:33,410
(They finish checking the calves' barn.)

952
00:35:34,010 --> 00:35:35,310
The red lights look so scary.

953
00:35:35,810 --> 00:35:38,410
(They head to the dairy barn, which is dyed in red.)

954
00:35:38,610 --> 00:35:41,149
Why did they use red lights only for this?

955
00:35:41,150 --> 00:35:42,380
Red lights are scary.

956
00:35:42,750 --> 00:35:44,990
Do cows find red lights relaxing?

957
00:35:45,590 --> 00:35:46,620
For their eyes?

958
00:35:46,790 --> 00:35:50,030
But cows go after red cloths.

959
00:35:50,860 --> 00:35:51,860
You're right.

960
00:35:51,960 --> 00:35:53,360
But... You're right.

961
00:35:53,700 --> 00:35:54,700
So cute.

962
00:35:54,760 --> 00:35:58,899
(The trainees have arrived at the dairy barn.)

963
00:35:58,900 --> 00:36:00,300
They're not sleeping.

964
00:36:00,640 --> 00:36:02,340
- They're not.
- They're not sleeping.

965
00:36:03,310 --> 00:36:05,940
It must be so scary.

966
00:36:06,310 --> 00:36:09,280
Look at that. This is impossible.

967
00:36:11,810 --> 00:36:14,320
(In the farm, where darkness falls)

968
00:36:15,880 --> 00:36:19,720
(As night gets deeper, the cows' cries grow louder.)

969
00:36:22,090 --> 00:36:26,600
(An unknown sound from an unknown place)

970
00:36:27,200 --> 00:36:31,130
(The barn looks eerie.)

971
00:36:32,470 --> 00:36:33,939
We need to check on the cow which hurt its legs.

972
00:36:33,940 --> 00:36:35,439
(The trainees muster up the courage to enter the dairy barn.)

973
00:36:35,440 --> 00:36:39,940
(Kyung Soo's camera)

974
00:36:41,410 --> 00:36:43,039
- My goodness!
- What?

975
00:36:43,040 --> 00:36:44,309
- What is it?
- What happened?

976
00:36:44,310 --> 00:36:46,150
- What?
- What is it?

977
00:36:46,450 --> 00:36:48,550
(It's the staff.)

978
00:36:49,450 --> 00:36:50,450
Goodness.

979
00:36:51,320 --> 00:36:52,390
I feel dizzy.

980
00:36:53,020 --> 00:36:54,760
How are you here on your own?

981
00:36:54,860 --> 00:36:55,920
Aren't you scared?

982
00:36:56,890 --> 00:36:57,989
(Woo Bin laughs in dismay.)

983
00:36:57,990 --> 00:37:00,130
How could he just sit here?

984
00:37:01,200 --> 00:37:02,700
(Woo Bin is amazed.)

985
00:37:02,930 --> 00:37:03,930
Darn it.

986
00:37:03,931 --> 00:37:06,200
(Trying to calm down his shocked heart)

987
00:37:07,070 --> 00:37:08,340
The hurt cows.

988
00:37:09,170 --> 00:37:10,410
Not the hurt cows.

989
00:37:10,970 --> 00:37:13,280
(They start their night patrol duty.)

990
00:37:13,980 --> 00:37:15,310
They're not asleep yet.

991
00:37:16,010 --> 00:37:18,709
(They came to check on the cow which fell.)

992
00:37:18,710 --> 00:37:19,710
How is it doing?

993
00:37:19,950 --> 00:37:21,780
- It's stood up.
- Is it sleeping?

994
00:37:22,050 --> 00:37:23,050
Are you okay?

995
00:37:23,051 --> 00:37:24,349
The legs have closed up a lot.

996
00:37:24,350 --> 00:37:25,350
Yes.

997
00:37:25,450 --> 00:37:26,789
Its legs used to tremble in the morning.

998
00:37:26,790 --> 00:37:28,190
Right, yesterday.

999
00:37:30,090 --> 00:37:31,960
- That was yesterday?
- Yes, yesterday.

1000
00:37:32,890 --> 00:37:33,899
It hurt its legs yesterday.

1001
00:37:33,900 --> 00:37:34,960
Really?

1002
00:37:35,460 --> 00:37:38,300
(It was today morning.)

1003
00:37:41,800 --> 00:37:44,370
The red lights are the mosquito lights.

1004
00:37:45,410 --> 00:37:46,469
It must chase away the mosquitoes.

1005
00:37:46,470 --> 00:37:48,940
Because white light attracts a lot of mosquitoes?

1006
00:37:49,710 --> 00:37:51,909
- To avoid attracting insects.
- I think so.

1007
00:37:51,910 --> 00:37:53,420
(They found out the purpose of the red lights.)

1008
00:37:54,180 --> 00:37:56,520
(They came to clean the barn.)

1009
00:37:57,020 --> 00:37:59,890
I'll do it myself. This is something I can do on my own.

1010
00:38:00,020 --> 00:38:02,060
(Intern Moon takes the initiative.)

1011
00:38:02,490 --> 00:38:05,290
Sang Hoon, use this.

1012
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:07,759
- This.
- This?

1013
00:38:07,760 --> 00:38:08,760
Yes.

1014
00:38:09,700 --> 00:38:12,000
- Sang Hoon.
- Yes?

1015
00:38:12,470 --> 00:38:13,699
Start on the other side...

1016
00:38:13,700 --> 00:38:15,470
- Okay.
- and make your way to here.

1017
00:38:15,570 --> 00:38:16,909
Push them into this.

1018
00:38:16,910 --> 00:38:18,070
I understand.

1019
00:38:18,870 --> 00:38:20,539
I'll work on my task.

1020
00:38:20,540 --> 00:38:21,540
Okay.

1021
00:38:21,580 --> 00:38:23,009
Hand me your camera.

1022
00:38:23,010 --> 00:38:24,010
Here.

1023
00:38:24,010 --> 00:38:25,010
(The intern shows off his spirits in the dark.)

1024
00:38:25,980 --> 00:38:29,890
(Sang Hoon starts sweeping as instructed.)

1025
00:38:30,450 --> 00:38:31,720
Let us go, Kwang Soo.

1026
00:38:31,920 --> 00:38:33,689
What more is here? It's right next door, right?

1027
00:38:33,690 --> 00:38:34,690
Yes.

1028
00:38:35,420 --> 00:38:39,230
(Sang Hoon is left alone like that.)

1029
00:38:41,960 --> 00:38:42,960
(Clanking)

1030
00:38:42,961 --> 00:38:43,970
Why?

1031
00:38:44,870 --> 00:38:46,900
(He freezes.)

1032
00:38:48,270 --> 00:38:50,910
What was that? It scared me.

1033
00:38:55,140 --> 00:38:57,510
(With his heart racing, he starts to sweep again.)

1034
00:39:01,020 --> 00:39:03,519
(He starts to sweep faster in fear.)

1035
00:39:03,520 --> 00:39:06,150
(Sighing)

1036
00:39:10,530 --> 00:39:12,130
What is that?

1037
00:39:12,330 --> 00:39:13,630
You scared me.

1038
00:39:13,730 --> 00:39:15,060
(It's me.)

1039
00:39:15,700 --> 00:39:17,100
You scared me.

1040
00:39:17,500 --> 00:39:20,700
(Sang Hoon was startled by the cow, which was eating its night snack.)

1041
00:39:22,900 --> 00:39:24,709
(Burp)

1042
00:39:24,710 --> 00:39:27,909
(Woo Bin laughs.)

1043
00:39:27,910 --> 00:39:29,080
He's getting startled by himself.

1044
00:39:31,480 --> 00:39:32,550
What was that?

1045
00:39:33,110 --> 00:39:36,149
I'm done.

1046
00:39:36,150 --> 00:39:40,160
(Although scared, the intern does his best.)

1047
00:39:40,320 --> 00:39:42,620
They continue to eat well even in this dark.

1048
00:39:43,160 --> 00:39:45,930
(Meanwhile, Woo Bin checks on the cows in the barn.)

1049
00:39:46,290 --> 00:39:48,699
(A loud noise)

1050
00:39:48,700 --> 00:39:49,700
What's this sound?

1051
00:39:51,670 --> 00:39:52,670
I see.

1052
00:39:53,440 --> 00:39:56,000
They go in there this late at night to get milked.

1053
00:39:56,100 --> 00:39:58,569
(With that, they end the barn patrol.)

1054
00:39:58,570 --> 00:40:00,839
(Night patrol duties: Clean the barn, check on the cows,)

1055
00:40:00,840 --> 00:40:03,110
(and check the temperature of the milk cooling tank.)

1056
00:40:03,280 --> 00:40:05,509
(Milk cooling tank, dairy barn, juvenile cows, calves)

1057
00:40:05,510 --> 00:40:07,220
Kwang Soo, I'll check.

1058
00:40:07,680 --> 00:40:10,519
(Kwang Soo and Kyung Soo came to check on the milk cooling tank.)

1059
00:40:10,520 --> 00:40:11,590
Below 5°C.

1060
00:40:13,920 --> 00:40:15,590
The set temperature...

1061
00:40:15,820 --> 00:40:17,690
- It needs to be below 5°C.
- is 4.3°C.

1062
00:40:17,790 --> 00:40:20,130
The current temperature is 3.9°C. That's good.

1063
00:40:20,330 --> 00:40:23,030
- Done.
- It's 3.9°C. Just nice.

1064
00:40:23,130 --> 00:40:24,929
(Check the temperature of the milk cooling tank.)

1065
00:40:24,930 --> 00:40:26,130
We're done.

1066
00:40:27,470 --> 00:40:29,699
(Kwang Soo and Kyung Soo come back.)

1067
00:40:29,700 --> 00:40:30,710
I'm done.

1068
00:40:31,570 --> 00:40:33,270
Gosh, I'm done.

1069
00:40:33,610 --> 00:40:35,340
You're sweating buckets.

1070
00:40:36,240 --> 00:40:38,180
- You're sweating so much.
- It's okay. I...

1071
00:40:38,580 --> 00:40:39,849
- We finished it regardless.
- Good job.

1072
00:40:39,850 --> 00:40:41,549
- Good job.
- Good job.

1073
00:40:41,550 --> 00:40:42,650
(They finished all the night patrol duties.)

1074
00:40:42,950 --> 00:40:44,489
I'm glad four of us came.

1075
00:40:44,490 --> 00:40:46,219
- I agree.
- I didn't expect this kind of vibe.

1076
00:40:46,220 --> 00:40:47,360
If only two came...

1077
00:40:47,690 --> 00:40:48,720
It wouldn't have been easy.

1078
00:40:49,320 --> 00:40:50,360
It'd be scary.

1079
00:40:51,930 --> 00:40:54,830
(The trainees exit the dairy barn after the patrol.)

1080
00:40:55,160 --> 00:40:56,870
Kwang Soo, look at the stars.

1081
00:40:57,430 --> 00:40:58,430
Shall we turn this off?

1082
00:40:58,431 --> 00:40:59,769
- Goodness.
- I can see so many.

1083
00:40:59,770 --> 00:41:02,299
- My gosh.
- I can see so many stars.

1084
00:41:02,300 --> 00:41:03,510
There are so many stars.

1085
00:41:04,340 --> 00:41:06,909
You can see a lot more when you take a photo with your phone.

1086
00:41:06,910 --> 00:41:08,079
- Really?
- Yes.

1087
00:41:08,080 --> 00:41:09,340
Let me take a photo with my phone.

1088
00:41:11,450 --> 00:41:12,450
Can you see lots?

1089
00:41:12,650 --> 00:41:14,720
It shook. Let me take another one.

1090
00:41:14,820 --> 00:41:16,119
(Kwang Soo and Woo Bin laugh.)

1091
00:41:16,120 --> 00:41:20,460
(The photos of stars taken from the members)

1092
00:41:21,760 --> 00:41:23,219
It looks like I'm on a retreat.

1093
00:41:23,220 --> 00:41:24,230
Right.

1094
00:41:26,130 --> 00:41:27,500
- Will the photo capture them?
- My gosh.

1095
00:41:28,230 --> 00:41:29,359
It's only possible in Jeju Island.

1096
00:41:29,360 --> 00:41:30,599
You can see the airplane too.

1097
00:41:30,600 --> 00:41:32,899
- You're right.
- Look at the Big Dipper.

1098
00:41:32,900 --> 00:41:33,940
You can see it so clearly.

1099
00:41:34,340 --> 00:41:36,039
- You're right.
- Like this.

1100
00:41:36,040 --> 00:41:37,610
One, two, three, four, five, six, seven.

1101
00:41:37,870 --> 00:41:40,440
There are so many stars.

1102
00:41:41,210 --> 00:41:42,980
They're so clear and visible.

1103
00:41:46,280 --> 00:41:47,280
Let's go, Kwang Soo.

1104
00:41:47,680 --> 00:41:48,720
Good night.

1105
00:41:49,050 --> 00:41:50,950
- Good night.
- Good night.

1106
00:41:51,250 --> 00:41:52,290
See you tomorrow.

1107
00:41:52,720 --> 00:41:55,159
(They finished the night patrol safely.)

1108
00:41:55,160 --> 00:41:56,459
They look at peace.

1109
00:41:56,460 --> 00:41:57,460
Yes.

1110
00:41:58,230 --> 00:42:00,700
It'd be hard with just two people.

1111
00:42:01,330 --> 00:42:02,900
The car... Who is it?

1112
00:42:03,330 --> 00:42:04,669
Mr. Kkalloo?

1113
00:42:04,670 --> 00:42:06,469
- Mr. Kkalloo.
- Hello.

1114
00:42:06,470 --> 00:42:08,070
- Hello.
- Where have you been?

1115
00:42:08,500 --> 00:42:11,039
I've been to Hamdeok.

1116
00:42:11,040 --> 00:42:12,970
- You've been to Hamdeok?
- You went to enjoy yourself.

1117
00:42:13,540 --> 00:42:15,579
- We finished the night duties.
- Sorry?

1118
00:42:15,580 --> 00:42:17,609
- The night patrol.
- Yes.

1119
00:42:17,610 --> 00:42:19,609
- And we...
- Should I join you?

1120
00:42:19,610 --> 00:42:21,250
No, we're done.

1121
00:42:21,980 --> 00:42:23,219
- See you tomorrow.
- Rest well.

1122
00:42:23,220 --> 00:42:24,249
- Good night.
- Good night.

1123
00:42:24,250 --> 00:42:26,149
- Rest well.
- Thank you.

1124
00:42:26,150 --> 00:42:27,820
(Putting behind the short meeting with the seniors)

1125
00:42:28,590 --> 00:42:30,260
Let's call the boss in front here.

1126
00:42:30,690 --> 00:42:31,859
Shall we call him as we go back?

1127
00:42:31,860 --> 00:42:32,930
Sure.

1128
00:42:36,060 --> 00:42:37,569
It's better to call the boss, right?

1129
00:42:37,570 --> 00:42:38,769
Yes, the boss.

1130
00:42:38,770 --> 00:42:41,140
I have a feeling the CEO is asleep.

1131
00:42:41,440 --> 00:42:42,640
Yes.

1132
00:42:48,140 --> 00:42:50,279
Hello?

1133
00:42:50,280 --> 00:42:52,209
- Hello, boss.
- Be quiet, Ji Woo.

1134
00:42:52,210 --> 00:42:54,420
- Hello?
- Hello, sir.

1135
00:42:54,820 --> 00:42:55,820
Hi.

1136
00:42:55,821 --> 00:42:59,120
We're calling you because we finished the night patrol.

1137
00:42:59,220 --> 00:43:01,720
I see. Did you run into any issue?

1138
00:43:02,090 --> 00:43:05,090
Not really. The calves are doing fine,

1139
00:43:05,190 --> 00:43:09,129
and the cow which injured its leg is standing up just fine...

1140
00:43:09,130 --> 00:43:10,200
and eating.

1141
00:43:10,300 --> 00:43:13,269
- Well...
- I see. Thanks for your hard work.

1142
00:43:13,270 --> 00:43:14,399
- Thank you.
- Good night.

1143
00:43:14,400 --> 00:43:15,499
- Good night.
- See you tomorrow.

1144
00:43:15,500 --> 00:43:16,600
- See you.
- See you.

1145
00:43:19,670 --> 00:43:21,010
Ji Woo must be crying.

1146
00:43:21,440 --> 00:43:24,050
She must be unhappy with something.

1147
00:43:25,480 --> 00:43:28,320
(They finish reporting their night patrol.)

1148
00:43:28,420 --> 00:43:31,519
Gosh, so many things happened today.

1149
00:43:31,520 --> 00:43:32,920
(After a long day, they finally arrive at the dorm.)

1150
00:43:33,350 --> 00:43:34,620
What do we need to do first?

1151
00:43:34,920 --> 00:43:36,020
Eat ramyeon.

1152
00:43:37,360 --> 00:43:40,360
(Food Director starts to boil the water first.)

1153
00:43:42,030 --> 00:43:46,130
(Cooking kimchi jjigae ramyeon)

1154
00:43:46,970 --> 00:43:48,700
(Canned tuna recommended by Sang Hoon)

1155
00:43:49,300 --> 00:43:52,510
(Mix ramyeon and tuna well.)

1156
00:43:52,710 --> 00:43:54,380
- Goodness.
- Let's go.

1157
00:43:54,680 --> 00:43:55,939
It looks so delicious.

1158
00:43:55,940 --> 00:43:57,650
(A night meal is ready in the blink of an eye.)

1159
00:43:58,010 --> 00:44:00,009
We're wearing matching shirts.

1160
00:44:00,010 --> 00:44:02,120
This looks like...

1161
00:44:02,820 --> 00:44:04,620
Everyone is wearing the same shirt.

1162
00:44:05,250 --> 00:44:06,250
(Taking a sip of soup)

1163
00:44:06,251 --> 00:44:08,290
The soup really tastes like that.

1164
00:44:09,760 --> 00:44:12,090
(Humming)

1165
00:44:12,390 --> 00:44:13,729
It really tastes like kimchi jjigae.

1166
00:44:13,730 --> 00:44:15,160
(Tuna kimchi jjigae-flavored ramyeon is well-received.)

1167
00:44:15,530 --> 00:44:17,569
They have cheese flavor too.

1168
00:44:17,570 --> 00:44:19,069
Then, we just...

1169
00:44:19,070 --> 00:44:20,439
- Just raw...
- It's cheese flavor?

1170
00:44:20,440 --> 00:44:21,700
- Yes, cheese.
- It looks so good.

1171
00:44:23,200 --> 00:44:25,369
There's cheese inside.

1172
00:44:25,370 --> 00:44:28,239
(Eating)

1173
00:44:28,240 --> 00:44:29,310
It's tasty.

1174
00:44:30,410 --> 00:44:32,549
The best part about this is...

1175
00:44:32,550 --> 00:44:34,580
that it's very simple.

1176
00:44:34,680 --> 00:44:37,290
You can carry it around and eat whenever you want.

1177
00:44:37,390 --> 00:44:39,019
- Keep it in the fridge and...
- Also,

1178
00:44:39,020 --> 00:44:40,120
it only has egg white.

1179
00:44:40,660 --> 00:44:42,619
Right. I don't eat egg yolks...

1180
00:44:42,620 --> 00:44:43,789
because of cholesterol.

1181
00:44:43,790 --> 00:44:46,090
They taste good together.

1182
00:44:46,190 --> 00:44:47,359
(It's a perfect pair with the spicy ramyeon.)

1183
00:44:47,360 --> 00:44:48,660
They're so good.

1184
00:44:48,760 --> 00:44:50,700
The cheese melts like this.

1185
00:44:52,470 --> 00:44:54,540
- It's so delicious.
- It is.

1186
00:44:57,010 --> 00:44:59,170
What game shall we play once we're done with ramyeon?

1187
00:44:59,970 --> 00:45:01,280
Did you play games yesterday?

1188
00:45:01,880 --> 00:45:04,580
Yesterday, we played around two hours.

1189
00:45:05,480 --> 00:45:08,079
(Solemn)

1190
00:45:08,080 --> 00:45:10,050
(Laughing)

1191
00:45:10,420 --> 00:45:11,449
It's 9:30pm.

1192
00:45:11,450 --> 00:45:12,719
(Current time: 9:30pm)

1193
00:45:12,720 --> 00:45:15,060
We have quite a bit of time.

1194
00:45:15,360 --> 00:45:16,590
Why don't we divide the team according to our rooms?

1195
00:45:17,460 --> 00:45:18,589
- Our rooms?
- Yes.

1196
00:45:18,590 --> 00:45:20,329
Since you wake your roommate up anyway?

1197
00:45:20,330 --> 00:45:21,600
- Yes.
- That's a good idea.

1198
00:45:22,000 --> 00:45:23,199
I tried to be super quiet,

1199
00:45:23,200 --> 00:45:24,200
but Kyung Soo woke up regardless.

1200
00:45:24,201 --> 00:45:25,429
(Kyung Soo is silent.)

1201
00:45:25,430 --> 00:45:26,900
You weren't quiet at all.

1202
00:45:27,200 --> 00:45:29,439
You practically stabbed me with your toothbrush...

1203
00:45:29,440 --> 00:45:31,210
- Really?
- when I was still sleeping.

1204
00:45:32,040 --> 00:45:33,710
- Was that today?
- Yes.

1205
00:45:34,440 --> 00:45:36,909
(Assigning the room using the stop watch)

1206
00:45:36,910 --> 00:45:39,210
(They're going to play 3 more games, so we'll fast-forward this.)

1207
00:45:39,710 --> 00:45:42,119
You and I are a team since we share a room.

1208
00:45:42,120 --> 00:45:43,249
I see.

1209
00:45:43,250 --> 00:45:44,319
- Okay.
- Let's switch seats.

1210
00:45:44,320 --> 00:45:46,289
(Roommates became teammates.)

1211
00:45:46,290 --> 00:45:48,159
(Double room, Woo bin and Kyung Soo, twin room, Kwang Soo and Sang Hoon)

1212
00:45:48,160 --> 00:45:49,689
I don't mind washing late today.

1213
00:45:49,690 --> 00:45:50,860
- Yes.
- But...

1214
00:45:50,960 --> 00:45:53,190
Woo Bin takes one hour to get ready.

1215
00:45:53,900 --> 00:45:54,900
- Which means...
- You need to...

1216
00:45:54,900 --> 00:45:55,900
wake up an hour earlier.

1217
00:45:55,900 --> 00:45:56,900
(The one that goes before Woo Bin needs to wake up 1 hour earlier.)

1218
00:45:56,901 --> 00:45:59,030
We need to play another game among ourselves.

1219
00:45:59,530 --> 00:46:02,270
The winner gets to wash and wake Kyung Soo up.

1220
00:46:02,800 --> 00:46:05,510
The loser wakes up an hour and a half earlier...

1221
00:46:05,840 --> 00:46:07,709
(Laughing)

1222
00:46:07,710 --> 00:46:09,280
To wake Woo Bin up.

1223
00:46:09,540 --> 00:46:11,310
It's a bit iffy to go back to sleep.

1224
00:46:11,980 --> 00:46:13,180
You'll sit down and do nothing.

1225
00:46:13,280 --> 00:46:15,180
(He can't hold his laughter back.)

1226
00:46:15,980 --> 00:46:17,320
While others are sleeping,

1227
00:46:18,090 --> 00:46:19,149
you could stretch.

1228
00:46:19,150 --> 00:46:20,219
(Laughing)

1229
00:46:20,220 --> 00:46:21,259
Really?

1230
00:46:21,260 --> 00:46:22,460
(Washing before Woo Bin is mind-blowing in many ways.)

1231
00:46:22,690 --> 00:46:23,730
What game shall we play?

1232
00:46:24,760 --> 00:46:26,589
Can I play one game which I've always wanted to?

1233
00:46:26,590 --> 00:46:27,900
Let's hear it out.

1234
00:46:29,700 --> 00:46:30,970
Charades.

1235
00:46:31,070 --> 00:46:32,629
(Laughing)

1236
00:46:32,630 --> 00:46:34,569
I'm just suggesting. This is...

1237
00:46:34,570 --> 00:46:37,409
Why do you want to play such an active game?

1238
00:46:37,410 --> 00:46:39,110
I really want to play it.

1239
00:46:39,910 --> 00:46:41,639
Must we?

1240
00:46:41,640 --> 00:46:43,110
(Sulking)

1241
00:46:43,340 --> 00:46:45,650
We woke up at 5am.

1242
00:46:46,450 --> 00:46:47,680
It's currently 10pm.

1243
00:46:48,180 --> 00:46:50,220
And you want to play Charades?

1244
00:46:51,090 --> 00:46:52,589
- Animals.
- Animals.

1245
00:46:52,590 --> 00:46:53,959
Something simple.

1246
00:46:53,960 --> 00:46:54,960
Yes, simple keywords.

1247
00:46:55,820 --> 00:46:56,890
What are you searching for?

1248
00:46:57,690 --> 00:46:59,489
- Gosh.
- Did you know about this app?

1249
00:46:59,490 --> 00:47:01,000
No, I looked it up.

1250
00:47:01,430 --> 00:47:03,299
Is the keyword provided at random?

1251
00:47:03,300 --> 00:47:04,300
It seems like it.

1252
00:47:04,500 --> 00:47:07,199
I'll put this up behind Kwang Soo.

1253
00:47:07,200 --> 00:47:08,270
- Yes.
- But he can see it.

1254
00:47:08,800 --> 00:47:10,710
I'll flip the cards from here.

1255
00:47:11,310 --> 00:47:12,640
- Can you see it?
- Come over here...

1256
00:47:12,910 --> 00:47:14,340
- with a chair.
- Got it.

1257
00:47:14,710 --> 00:47:16,710
The one who has to act it out is the one...

1258
00:47:17,010 --> 00:47:18,149
reading the keyword, right?

1259
00:47:18,150 --> 00:47:19,979
- Yes.
- Not the guesser.

1260
00:47:19,980 --> 00:47:21,180
(The beginner gaming club still has a long way to go.)

1261
00:47:21,420 --> 00:47:23,279
I'll take clips of you with that camera.

1262
00:47:23,280 --> 00:47:24,290
- Okay.
- Good.

1263
00:47:25,190 --> 00:47:27,720
(Trying to decide on the order of their showers)

1264
00:47:28,020 --> 00:47:29,390
I'll come over here first,

1265
00:47:30,390 --> 00:47:31,489
and then scan everyone else.

1266
00:47:31,490 --> 00:47:32,490
(Setting up for the game Charades)

1267
00:47:32,890 --> 00:47:35,000
(Role 1: Keyword)

1268
00:47:35,100 --> 00:47:36,329
You can take Sang Hoon for now.

1269
00:47:36,330 --> 00:47:37,700
- With this?
- Okay.

1270
00:47:38,930 --> 00:47:40,799
- Right now...
- If the flow gets interrupted...

1271
00:47:40,800 --> 00:47:42,400
- I know.
- You get it, right?

1272
00:47:42,500 --> 00:47:43,639
(Kwang Soo's camera)

1273
00:47:43,640 --> 00:47:45,209
Ready. Should I do it?

1274
00:47:45,210 --> 00:47:46,310
(Role 4: Actor)

1275
00:47:47,110 --> 00:47:48,940
- Tell me when you're ready.
- I'm ready.

1276
00:47:49,210 --> 00:47:50,650
Set, go.

1277
00:47:51,080 --> 00:47:53,080
(After setting the 1-minute timer)

1278
00:47:53,450 --> 00:47:55,779
(Showing the camera the keyword)

1279
00:47:55,780 --> 00:47:57,320
(Checking the keyword)

1280
00:47:57,490 --> 00:47:59,619
(Try to guess it together!)

1281
00:47:59,620 --> 00:48:00,620
Sloth.

1282
00:48:01,460 --> 00:48:02,660
(A shell?)

1283
00:48:03,490 --> 00:48:04,830
(Slow)

1284
00:48:06,160 --> 00:48:07,160
Try guessing it.

1285
00:48:07,960 --> 00:48:08,960
Look at his fingers.

1286
00:48:09,300 --> 00:48:10,360
Turtle. Terrapin.

1287
00:48:11,470 --> 00:48:12,969
(The next keyword)

1288
00:48:12,970 --> 00:48:14,199
(Two bowls)

1289
00:48:14,200 --> 00:48:15,200
(Slurping)

1290
00:48:15,700 --> 00:48:16,700
Jjamjjamyeon.

1291
00:48:17,970 --> 00:48:18,970
(Jjamjjamyeon)

1292
00:48:18,971 --> 00:48:20,540
(Impressed)

1293
00:48:20,910 --> 00:48:21,979
(The next keyword)

1294
00:48:21,980 --> 00:48:23,079
(Slamming down a hammer)

1295
00:48:23,080 --> 00:48:24,449
(Flashing?)

1296
00:48:24,450 --> 00:48:25,450
Thor.

1297
00:48:26,280 --> 00:48:27,319
Thor.

1298
00:48:27,320 --> 00:48:28,620
(Amazed)

1299
00:48:29,150 --> 00:48:31,150
(It's another food keyword.)

1300
00:48:31,420 --> 00:48:33,519
(He's suddenly sleeping?)

1301
00:48:33,520 --> 00:48:34,790
Instant noodles?

1302
00:48:35,190 --> 00:48:36,190
Jjajangmyeon?

1303
00:48:37,890 --> 00:48:40,029
(Just when Team Kwang Soo and Sang Hoon is on a roll,)

1304
00:48:40,030 --> 00:48:42,700
(a Western instrument suddenly appears.)

1305
00:48:43,200 --> 00:48:45,269
(Hoonysos)

1306
00:48:45,270 --> 00:48:46,330
Double bass?

1307
00:48:46,770 --> 00:48:47,999
(Double bass?)

1308
00:48:48,000 --> 00:48:49,000
Pass.

1309
00:48:49,001 --> 00:48:50,200
(Passing after "double bass")

1310
00:48:51,410 --> 00:48:53,170
(Their specialty is back.)

1311
00:48:54,680 --> 00:48:56,139
(Jjajang, tangsuyuk sauce)

1312
00:48:56,140 --> 00:48:57,580
(Dipping)

1313
00:48:58,580 --> 00:49:00,579
- Okay, the end.
- That wasn't bad.

1314
00:49:00,580 --> 00:49:02,450
- Gosh.
- They're good.

1315
00:49:03,150 --> 00:49:04,349
How did you get jjamjjamyeon?

1316
00:49:04,350 --> 00:49:05,790
Sang Hoon split it into two.

1317
00:49:06,150 --> 00:49:07,320
Earlier,

1318
00:49:07,390 --> 00:49:09,620
the last meal before death...

1319
00:49:10,490 --> 00:49:11,589
What did he do?

1320
00:49:11,590 --> 00:49:12,689
(Before you die)

1321
00:49:12,690 --> 00:49:13,759
(Slurping)

1322
00:49:13,760 --> 00:49:16,030
Out of the blue... It didn't even cross my mind.

1323
00:49:16,500 --> 00:49:18,630
But I thought, "The dish I mentioned I'd eat before dying?"

1324
00:49:19,530 --> 00:49:21,370
You two have great chemistry.

1325
00:49:21,700 --> 00:49:23,239
Sang Hoon, you're great at it.

1326
00:49:23,240 --> 00:49:25,039
(Feeling shy)

1327
00:49:25,040 --> 00:49:26,170
