(The cows are mooing loudly this morning.)

1590
00:58:49,139 --> 00:58:50,139
They're mooing again.

1591
00:58:50,979 --> 00:58:52,008
For food.

1592
00:58:52,009 --> 00:58:53,349
A few days ago...

1593
00:58:53,809 --> 00:58:54,849
Farmfarm's mom.

1594
00:58:55,949 --> 00:58:57,319
Who can tell which cow is which...

1595
00:58:58,219 --> 00:58:59,219
by the mooing, right?

1596
00:58:59,949 --> 00:59:01,189
Everyone's up.

1597
00:59:01,789 --> 00:59:03,858
- The cows are waiting for us.
- They were sleeping earlier.

1598
00:59:03,859 --> 00:59:05,058
(The cows are waiting for breakfast.)

1599
00:59:05,059 --> 00:59:07,589
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

1600
00:59:08,699 --> 00:59:09,929
Good morning.

1601
00:59:10,499 --> 00:59:11,798
- Mr. Lal.
- Mr. Lal.

1602
00:59:11,799 --> 00:59:12,868
(Lal is out early this morning.)

1603
00:59:12,869 --> 00:59:14,069
He's dolled up today.

1604
00:59:14,669 --> 00:59:15,699
Isn't he?

1605
00:59:16,369 --> 00:59:18,869
Kwang Soo asked him why he slept yesterday during working time.

1606
00:59:19,269 --> 00:59:21,578
That must be why he dressed up a little today.

1607
00:59:21,579 --> 00:59:23,579
- Right. Mr. Lal...
- Yes?

1608
00:59:23,939 --> 00:59:25,578
- went downtown yesterday.
- Right.

1609
00:59:25,579 --> 00:59:26,649
Did you see his hair styled?

1610
00:59:26,979 --> 00:59:29,278
- Really?
- Hamdeok. He went to Hamdeok.

1611
00:59:29,279 --> 00:59:30,548
- It was too dark for me to see.
- Was his hair styled?

1612
00:59:30,549 --> 00:59:32,318
Yes, his hair looked all fancy.

1613
00:59:32,319 --> 00:59:33,349
- Did he use hair gel?
- Did he use hair gel?

1614
00:59:34,149 --> 00:59:36,089
I think it was hair wax.

1615
00:59:36,759 --> 00:59:39,659
(Arrived at the farmer's hut while chit-chatting)

1616
00:59:41,099 --> 00:59:42,128
Sang Hoon, are you going to wear...

1617
00:59:42,129 --> 00:59:43,159
- the straw hat?
- Yes.

1618
00:59:43,359 --> 00:59:44,768
- Then I will too.
- I'll wear this one.

1619
00:59:44,769 --> 00:59:48,068
(KKPP hat)

1620
00:59:48,069 --> 00:59:49,269
My cowboy hat...

1621
00:59:50,939 --> 00:59:52,208
- What?
- kept flying away...

1622
00:59:52,209 --> 00:59:53,469
in the wind yesterday.

1623
00:59:55,109 --> 00:59:58,909
(Everyone is putting on their cowboy hats.)

1624
01:00:00,949 --> 01:00:04,648
(Rejected)

1625
01:00:04,649 --> 01:00:07,288
(Kwang Soo moves the baseball cap away from Kyung Soo's sight.)

1626
01:00:07,289 --> 01:00:08,419
That's...

1627
01:00:08,659 --> 01:00:10,659
I'm going to wear that hat.

1628
01:00:11,629 --> 01:00:12,729
Let's wear it after work.

1629
01:00:14,129 --> 01:00:15,229
It looks really good on you.

1630
01:00:16,599 --> 01:00:20,298
(Kyung Soo ends up wearing the cowboy hat.)

1631
01:00:20,299 --> 01:00:23,599
I feel as if we've become actual farm workers.

1632
01:00:24,069 --> 01:00:25,468
Good morning, sir.

1633
01:00:25,469 --> 01:00:26,938
- Good morning, sir.
- Good morning, sir.

1634
01:00:26,939 --> 01:00:28,009
Good morning.

1635
01:00:29,309 --> 01:00:30,909
- Did you have a restful night?
- Yes.

1636
01:00:32,049 --> 01:00:33,778
- Good morning.
- Did you sleep well?

1637
01:00:33,779 --> 01:00:34,779
- Yes.
- Yes.

1638
01:00:34,780 --> 01:00:35,918
(Morning Task Schedule: Wash the feeding bowls.)

1639
01:00:35,919 --> 01:00:37,079
They're asking for food.

1640
01:00:38,149 --> 01:00:40,948
(Naturally taking the cleaning tools)

1641
01:00:40,949 --> 01:00:43,358
(Get cleaning already!)

1642
01:00:43,359 --> 01:00:47,129
(Cleaning the feeding bowls with Kyung Soo in the lead)

1643
01:00:47,229 --> 01:00:49,958
(After the first person blows everything out,)

1644
01:00:49,959 --> 01:00:53,268
(the next person pushes the hay with a shovel.)

1645
01:00:53,269 --> 01:00:54,299
This is a little too much.

1646
01:00:55,739 --> 01:00:56,938
Sang Hoon, take the first half.

1647
01:00:56,939 --> 01:00:57,939
Got it.

1648
01:00:59,409 --> 01:01:02,308
(The intern works hard on his first-ever feeding bowl cleanup.)

1649
01:01:02,309 --> 01:01:06,049
(The experienced workers are masters at it.)

1650
01:01:06,649 --> 01:01:09,378
(We're hungry!)

1651
01:01:09,379 --> 01:01:11,548
What's wrong?

1652
01:01:11,549 --> 01:01:12,549
Okay.

1653
01:01:13,519 --> 01:01:16,619
(Checking the hungry cows' conditions in between)

1654
01:01:17,359 --> 01:01:20,788
(Why are you only watching today?)

1655
01:01:20,789 --> 01:01:22,098
Of course. They were trained.

1656
01:01:22,099 --> 01:01:23,399
I'm supervising to see if they're doing it well.

1657
01:01:24,059 --> 01:01:27,228
(A relaxing morning thanks to the trainees)

1658
01:01:27,229 --> 01:01:28,699
- Sang Hoon, like this.
- Yes?

1659
01:01:28,839 --> 01:01:29,869
Got it.

1660
01:01:32,139 --> 01:01:35,109
(Scooping the hay nonstop just like his senior trainees)

1661
01:01:39,149 --> 01:01:41,618
(It's been a long morning already.)

1662
01:01:41,619 --> 01:01:42,879
This looks like green onion salad.

1663
01:01:43,721 --> 01:01:45,860
(An imagination befitting a foodie)

1664
01:01:45,861 --> 01:01:50,060
(Finished cleaning the feeding bowls)

1665
01:01:50,061 --> 01:01:51,101
Let's make their feed.

1666
01:01:51,671 --> 01:01:53,531
Sir, we'll get on with mixing it.

1667
01:01:53,801 --> 01:01:55,141
Let's add the powder first.

1668
01:01:56,441 --> 01:01:57,471
Add 120kg of it.

1669
01:01:58,211 --> 01:01:59,211
(With the Food Director leading, they start mixing the feed.)

1670
01:01:59,212 --> 01:02:00,741
- Did you set the scale?
- Yes.

1671
01:02:01,141 --> 01:02:03,510
If it's 120kg... Is there a scale?

1672
01:02:03,511 --> 01:02:04,511
Yes, over here.

1673
01:02:04,512 --> 01:02:05,911
It's a lot more than you think.

1674
01:02:06,911 --> 01:02:08,680
(The intern is keeping up well...)

1675
01:02:08,681 --> 01:02:10,420
(despite doing it for the first time.)

1676
01:02:10,421 --> 01:02:11,490
It smells good.

1677
01:02:11,491 --> 01:02:13,051
- It's corn.
- Corn powder.

1678
01:02:15,121 --> 01:02:16,590
It's like sucking on your fingers...

1679
01:02:16,591 --> 01:02:18,091
- after eating popcorn.
- Exactly.

1680
01:02:19,161 --> 01:02:23,400
(The ingredient stimulates the Food Intern's appetite.)

1681
01:02:23,401 --> 01:02:24,431
Cottonseeds?

1682
01:02:24,601 --> 01:02:25,701
- Okay.
- Cottonseeds?

1683
01:02:26,631 --> 01:02:27,701
Cottonseeds, right?

1684
01:02:28,201 --> 01:02:29,300
- Yes.
- Correct.

1685
01:02:29,301 --> 01:02:33,210
(The second ingredient is cottonseeds.)

1686
01:02:33,211 --> 01:02:36,341
My ancestors brought this in.

1687
01:02:37,381 --> 01:02:38,450
Are you a descendant of Mun Ik Chom?

1688
01:02:38,451 --> 01:02:39,481
Yes.

1689
01:02:39,781 --> 01:02:40,981
- For real?
- Yes.

1690
01:02:42,751 --> 01:02:45,890
(The descendant of Mun Ik Chom feels proud.)

1691
01:02:45,891 --> 01:02:46,920
Should we add this one next?

1692
01:02:46,921 --> 01:02:48,421
- It's super windy today.
- Right?

1693
01:02:49,161 --> 01:02:50,720
(It's time to add the hay bales.)

1694
01:02:50,721 --> 01:02:51,761
One.

1695
01:02:52,861 --> 01:02:53,891
Six.

1696
01:02:56,761 --> 01:02:58,171
(Coughing)

1697
01:02:58,471 --> 01:02:59,471
Sorry.

1698
01:03:00,501 --> 01:03:01,501
One left, right?

1699
01:03:01,502 --> 01:03:02,671
- I'll do it.
- No, I will.

1700
01:03:03,701 --> 01:03:04,911
- Is that it?
- Yes.

1701
01:03:07,311 --> 01:03:08,781
What was our next task?

1702
01:03:09,941 --> 01:03:12,681
(Add in more hay.)

1703
01:03:13,151 --> 01:03:15,880
(While Woo Bin and Sang Hoon are putting in hay)

1704
01:03:15,881 --> 01:03:18,921
You have to dig in a little to get the net out.

1705
01:03:19,091 --> 01:03:20,091
(Kwang Soo and Kyung Soo rip the net out of the big hay bale.)

1706
01:03:20,092 --> 01:03:21,291
We have to unroll it.

1707
01:03:21,561 --> 01:03:22,761
All done.

1708
01:03:24,321 --> 01:03:27,560
(Getting the task done easily as the four work together)

1709
01:03:27,561 --> 01:03:31,400
(Finished adding the hay in no time)

1710
01:03:31,401 --> 01:03:32,771
What's next?

1711
01:03:33,631 --> 01:03:34,641
Are we done?

1712
01:03:35,441 --> 01:03:37,470
Salt! Salt, right?

1713
01:03:37,471 --> 01:03:38,471
- Salt.
- Yes, salt.

1714
01:03:39,111 --> 01:03:41,141
- Two-thirds of the bag.
- Two-thirds?

1715
01:03:41,611 --> 01:03:43,980
(Seasoning the feed with salt)

1716
01:03:43,981 --> 01:03:45,181
Soybean meal, 70kg.

1717
01:03:46,311 --> 01:03:47,380
It's going to get dusty.

1718
01:03:47,381 --> 01:03:48,451
- Be careful.
- Okay.

1719
01:03:49,521 --> 01:03:51,790
(Adding in the soybean meal)

1720
01:03:51,791 --> 01:03:53,321
We're getting this done in no time.

1721
01:03:56,221 --> 01:03:57,820
All done. We finished it in one go.

1722
01:03:57,821 --> 01:03:59,030
(Done with 70kg of soybean meal)

1723
01:03:59,031 --> 01:04:00,391
- Finished.
- Nice.

1724
01:04:00,491 --> 01:04:01,661
Perfect.

1725
01:04:02,231 --> 01:04:04,501
- We were faster than yesterday.
- For sure.

1726
01:04:05,531 --> 01:04:07,400
(You call this fast?)

1727
01:04:07,401 --> 01:04:08,871
Push the button, and we're done for the corn, right?

1728
01:04:10,671 --> 01:04:14,780
(Done making the feed fast)

1729
01:04:14,781 --> 01:04:16,641
I'm quite surprised at myself.

1730
01:04:17,211 --> 01:04:19,650
(Proud of how much he improved in just a day)

1731
01:04:19,651 --> 01:04:21,580
It's less tiresome than yesterday.

1732
01:04:21,581 --> 01:04:23,121
Of course. You got used to it.

1733
01:04:24,121 --> 01:04:25,291
You're quick to adapt.

1734
01:04:26,651 --> 01:04:27,950
Is it because we have Sang Hoon?

1735
01:04:27,951 --> 01:04:29,120
Yes, probably.

1736
01:04:29,121 --> 01:04:30,960
- You weren't here yesterday.
- Sang Hoon wasn't here...

1737
01:04:30,961 --> 01:04:31,961
in the morning.

1738
01:04:32,931 --> 01:04:34,390
- No wonder.
- What a big difference.

1739
01:04:34,391 --> 01:04:35,400
- Really?
- For real.

1740
01:04:35,401 --> 01:04:37,231
Did I do my part?

1741
01:04:38,071 --> 01:04:39,971
Yesterday was tough.

1742
01:04:40,031 --> 01:04:42,400
- True.
- Was it the same job?

1743
01:04:42,401 --> 01:04:43,441
Yes, the same one.

1744
01:04:43,871 --> 01:04:45,270
- It took much longer.
- Let's blow the dust off.

1745
01:04:45,271 --> 01:04:46,711
I thought we had gotten used to the job.

1746
01:04:47,171 --> 01:04:49,840
(Kyung Soo's new way of using the air blower)

1747
01:04:49,841 --> 01:04:52,181
Turn around for me. Turn around.

1748
01:04:53,111 --> 01:04:57,051
(KKPP Food's outstanding aftercare)

1749
01:05:00,651 --> 01:05:04,521
(He can't help but make fun of Kwang Soo.)

1750
01:05:05,591 --> 01:05:09,731
(Okay, got it.)

1751
01:05:11,261 --> 01:05:13,801
(Going straight for the face after pretending to dust off his clothes)

1752
01:05:14,801 --> 01:05:18,411
(Kyung Soo pays the price.)

1753
01:05:19,971 --> 01:05:22,040
(You thought it was over, didn't you?)

1754
01:05:22,041 --> 01:05:25,510
(Laughing)

1755
01:05:25,511 --> 01:05:26,981
- Doesn't it feel nice?
- It does.

1756
01:05:27,951 --> 01:05:30,381
(It was a satisfying service.)

1757
01:05:30,451 --> 01:05:32,520
I'll feed the cows on this side.

1758
01:05:32,521 --> 01:05:33,590
(Time to give out breakfast)

1759
01:05:33,591 --> 01:05:35,221
Sang Hoon, the cows are waiting with their heads out.

1760
01:05:36,061 --> 01:05:37,360
(The cows are ready to dig in.)

1761
01:05:37,361 --> 01:05:40,890
It's mixed with what the cows love.

1762
01:05:40,891 --> 01:05:42,001
I see.

1763
01:05:42,101 --> 01:05:43,500
They pick those ingredients out.

1764
01:05:43,501 --> 01:05:45,331
- Just like ham in fried rice.
- Yes.

1765
01:05:46,031 --> 01:05:47,130
Look at them going through it.

1766
01:05:47,131 --> 01:05:48,140
(Peeking)

1767
01:05:48,141 --> 01:05:49,300
Its leg looks much better.

1768
01:05:49,301 --> 01:05:50,500
Right? It's walking well.

1769
01:05:50,501 --> 01:05:51,610
(The cow that injured its leg the day before)

1770
01:05:51,611 --> 01:05:52,971
- It's walking just fine.
- Yes.

1771
01:05:53,711 --> 01:05:55,640
(Relieved to see it walking well)

1772
01:05:55,641 --> 01:05:57,111
- They sure are digging in.
- Right?

1773
01:05:57,341 --> 01:05:59,281
Look at them enjoying it. They must've been hungry.

1774
01:05:59,781 --> 01:06:01,650
The cows are only picking out the corn.

1775
01:06:01,651 --> 01:06:03,751
I'm sure cows also like tasty food.

1776
01:06:04,021 --> 01:06:07,021
It's digging into the feed like this...

1777
01:06:08,021 --> 01:06:10,361
and picking out the corn with their tongues.

1778
01:06:11,191 --> 01:06:14,190
(You were good at mixing the feed.)

1779
01:06:14,191 --> 01:06:16,401
I was, right? It's because we did it yesterday.

1780
01:06:16,701 --> 01:06:17,731
It feels rewarding...

1781
01:06:18,201 --> 01:06:20,531
to watch the cows dig in.

1782
01:06:21,031 --> 01:06:23,601
I didn't know cows love food.

1783
01:06:24,541 --> 01:06:28,141
(Meanwhile, the intern is taking selfies with the cows.)

1784
01:06:28,241 --> 01:06:31,780
(He must want to capture this hardworking moment.)

1785
01:06:31,781 --> 01:06:33,681
- Should I take one for you?
- Yes, please.

1786
01:06:33,711 --> 01:06:34,711
Okay.

1787
01:06:34,712 --> 01:06:36,780
Stand in the middle just like that.

1788
01:06:36,781 --> 01:06:37,821
Okay.

1789
01:06:38,821 --> 01:06:39,821
In the middle.

1790
01:06:39,822 --> 01:06:41,860
(The CEO and the auditor want to take a photo of the intern.)

1791
01:06:41,861 --> 01:06:43,061
Stop there.

1792
01:06:43,861 --> 01:06:45,590
(They're even paying attention to positioning.)

1793
01:06:45,591 --> 01:06:46,731
That looks perfect.

1794
01:06:47,961 --> 01:06:49,930
(Mischief kicks in.)

1795
01:06:49,931 --> 01:06:52,771
That looks good. Can you pose differently?

1796
01:06:53,871 --> 01:06:57,641
(Sang Hoon is absorbed in posing for the camera.)

1797
01:06:58,211 --> 01:06:59,540
(Smiling)

1798
01:06:59,541 --> 01:07:00,611
Wait.

1799
01:07:02,541 --> 01:07:03,541
That looks great.

1800
01:07:05,581 --> 01:07:08,220
Hold it. One, two, three.

1801
01:07:08,221 --> 01:07:09,221
(They're serious about making fun of the intern.)

1802
01:07:09,221 --> 01:07:10,221
It's done.

1803
01:07:10,421 --> 01:07:11,421
Thank you.

1804
01:07:12,391 --> 01:07:13,521
- Take a look.
- Okay.

1805
01:07:15,121 --> 01:07:18,090
(Checking the photos)

1806
01:07:18,091 --> 01:07:19,560
(He figures out the truth behind the photos.)

1807
01:07:19,561 --> 01:07:20,690
Thank you.

1808
01:07:20,691 --> 01:07:22,101
There are more.

1809
01:07:22,931 --> 01:07:24,831
- It came out well.
- Thank you.

1810
01:07:25,301 --> 01:07:26,670
Shall we take a selfie here?

1811
01:07:26,671 --> 01:07:28,070
- Yes.
- Sang Hoon.

1812
01:07:28,071 --> 01:07:29,240
- Let's take a selfie.
- Let's take another photo.

1813
01:07:29,241 --> 01:07:30,301
- All right.
- The four of us.

1814
01:07:30,971 --> 01:07:34,270
(Taking a photo of themselves after working hard)

1815
01:07:34,271 --> 01:07:35,940
Shouldn't there be cows in the background?

1816
01:07:35,941 --> 01:07:36,980
You're right.

1817
01:07:36,981 --> 01:07:38,580
Thank you.

1818
01:07:38,581 --> 01:07:39,651
We're done.

1819
01:07:40,751 --> 01:07:42,350
I think we have some free time now.

1820
01:07:42,351 --> 01:07:45,391
Woo Bin, why don't we divide the work?

1821
01:07:45,591 --> 01:07:47,291
- Okay.
- Instead of just waiting,

1822
01:07:47,851 --> 01:07:49,391
- why don't we...
- That's an excellent idea.

1823
01:07:49,491 --> 01:07:50,521
How about this?

1824
01:07:51,661 --> 01:07:54,361
Kwang Soo and Sang Hoon,

1825
01:07:54,661 --> 01:07:56,600
- take care of the work here.
- Okay.

1826
01:07:56,601 --> 01:07:58,630
Let's go and clean up the manure.

1827
01:07:58,631 --> 01:07:59,731
Let's go.

1828
01:08:00,031 --> 01:08:02,301
We'll clean up the manure and milk the cows.

1829
01:08:02,401 --> 01:08:04,001
Once you're done here, please join us.

1830
01:08:04,101 --> 01:08:05,410
(The director leaves after giving orders naturally.)

1831
01:08:05,411 --> 01:08:06,640
(Spacing out)

1832
01:08:06,641 --> 01:08:08,980
It seems like the director is giving all orders.

1833
01:08:08,981 --> 01:08:10,641
Not exactly.

1834
01:08:10,741 --> 01:08:12,350
I was going to do it.

1835
01:08:12,351 --> 01:08:16,051
I was going to do the work anyway.

1836
01:08:16,151 --> 01:08:17,721
Was it necessary to say it out loud?

1837
01:08:17,921 --> 01:08:19,891
If you think of it as being ordered around, there's no end to it.

1838
01:08:21,451 --> 01:08:22,761
Our company is open-minded.

1839
01:08:24,291 --> 01:08:27,391
I'm the CEO, and he's the intern,

1840
01:08:28,331 --> 01:08:29,361
but we're all equal.

1841
01:08:29,931 --> 01:08:31,730
You tend to look at the big picture.

1842
01:08:31,731 --> 01:08:32,870
- Right.
- The director handles...

1843
01:08:32,871 --> 01:08:34,000
the day-to-day details.

1844
01:08:34,001 --> 01:08:35,071
Exactly.

1845
01:08:36,401 --> 01:08:39,170
If I only had focused on one tree, I wouldn't have made it this far.

1846
01:08:39,171 --> 01:08:40,171
He's right.

1847
01:08:40,941 --> 01:08:42,640
- Running the machine could be...
- Yes.

1848
01:08:42,641 --> 01:08:44,341
- still dangerous for you.
- Okay.

1849
01:08:50,251 --> 01:08:53,350
(The CEO shows his intern his reassuring side.)

1850
01:08:53,351 --> 01:08:55,261
There's less manure than yesterday.

1851
01:08:56,021 --> 01:08:57,290
- Isn't there less?
- Yes.

1852
01:08:57,291 --> 01:08:58,790
(They're busy cleaning up the manure.)

1853
01:08:58,791 --> 01:09:00,891
Their manure doesn't look like poop anymore.

1854
01:09:01,701 --> 01:09:02,901
It looks more like mud.

1855
01:09:03,531 --> 01:09:04,901
I said the same thing yesterday.

1856
01:09:06,001 --> 01:09:07,971
It's not easy getting used to manure,

1857
01:09:08,571 --> 01:09:10,371
