- What?

1910
01:11:17,731 --> 01:11:19,400
I stopped myself from mopping.

1911
01:11:19,401 --> 01:11:20,600
(I see.)

1912
01:11:20,601 --> 01:11:22,000
That's how dedicated I feel.

1913
01:11:22,001 --> 01:11:23,071
It's okay.

1914
01:11:24,271 --> 01:11:25,771
There's more out here.

1915
01:11:26,971 --> 01:11:29,541
Sang Hoon, you're doing an excellent job.

1916
01:11:30,941 --> 01:11:32,681
The intern has a knack for the job.

1917
01:11:33,181 --> 01:11:35,081
I did exactly what the CEO told me to do.

1918
01:11:35,181 --> 01:11:37,351
Hey, don't be so modest.

1919
01:11:38,021 --> 01:11:39,550
You should take credit for your own work.

1920
01:11:39,551 --> 01:11:40,820
(The CEO and the intern make a great team.)

1921
01:11:40,821 --> 01:11:42,521
Are you done? Shall we go and feed them?

1922
01:11:43,991 --> 01:11:44,991
Once we do this...

1923
01:11:45,391 --> 01:11:46,531
- and graze them...
- Then, we're done.

1924
01:11:46,991 --> 01:11:49,401
The milk might overflow, so pull it gently.

1925
01:11:50,101 --> 01:11:52,271
Aren't you used to the work now?

1926
01:11:52,501 --> 01:11:53,501
Yes.

1927
01:11:53,502 --> 01:11:55,270
(The trainees became true ranch workers.)

1928
01:11:55,271 --> 01:11:56,841
When they hear the sound of these wheels,

1929
